WEBVTT

00:16.350 --> 00:17.751
[SEAGULLS SQUAWK, HORN BELLOWS]

00:17.751 --> 00:18.952
Radio announcer: RIGHT NOW,
IT'S CURRENTLY

00:18.952 --> 00:20.454
AT 65 DEGREES THIS MORNING

00:20.454 --> 00:22.690
WITH TEMPERATURES RISING
INTO THE LOW 80s

00:22.690 --> 00:24.325
IN DOWNTOWN LOS ANGELES.

00:24.325 --> 00:27.027
EXPECT COASTAL FOG
AND A HIGH SURF ADVISORY

00:27.027 --> 00:29.430
FROM LONG BEACH
ALL THE WAY TO LAGUNA.

00:29.430 --> 00:31.299
SO, GET YOUR SURFBOARDS OUT

00:31.299 --> 00:34.568
AND GET READY FOR ANOTHER
SOUTHLAND SUMMER DAY.

01:12.240 --> 01:14.442
[ALARM CLOCK BUZZES]

01:41.635 --> 01:44.138
[GROWLS, WHIMPERS]

01:47.841 --> 01:50.110
[DOG BARKS]

01:50.110 --> 01:51.712
[BARKS]

01:54.282 --> 01:58.419
* WOKE UP TODAY *

01:58.419 --> 02:03.123
* TO EVERYTHING GREY *

02:03.123 --> 02:07.661
* AND ALL THAT I SAW *

02:07.661 --> 02:13.667
* JUST KEPT GOIN'
ON AND ON *

02:13.667 --> 02:20.408
* SWEEP ALL THE PIECES
UNDER THE BED *

02:23.043 --> 02:25.012
* CLOSE ALL THE CURTAINS *

02:25.012 --> 02:27.615
* AND COVER MY HEAD *

02:27.615 --> 02:30.050
* AND WHAT YOU WISH FOR *

02:30.050 --> 02:32.052
* WON'T COME TRUE *

02:32.052 --> 02:34.255
* YOU AREN'T
SURPRISED, LOVE *

02:34.255 --> 02:39.026
* ARE YOU? *

02:39.026 --> 02:40.361
Coleen: ALYSSA.

02:44.332 --> 02:45.899
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

02:48.802 --> 02:49.670
* IT'S NOT WHAT *

02:49.670 --> 02:52.172
* YOU WANT *
[CLOCK BEEPS]

02:52.172 --> 02:58.045
* IT'S JUST HOW IT IS *

02:58.045 --> 03:03.984
* IT KEEPS GOIN' ON AND ON *

03:03.984 --> 03:10.958
* COME OUT, COME OUT
WHEREVER YOU ARE *

03:12.626 --> 03:17.898
* WOULD YOU DO IT ALL OVER
RIGHT FROM THE START? *

03:17.898 --> 03:22.436
* AND WHAT YOU WISH FOR
WON'T COME TRUE *

03:22.436 --> 03:24.738
* YOU AREN'T
SURPRISED, LOVE *

03:24.738 --> 03:29.410
* ARE YOU? *

03:34.348 --> 03:35.349
[INHALES]

03:35.349 --> 03:39.453
* ONCE HAD THIS DREAM *

03:39.453 --> 03:44.858
* CRASHED DOWN AND UP *

03:46.694 --> 03:47.995
I WANT YOU TO GO
GIVE YOUR DAD A HUG.

03:47.995 --> 03:49.196
WHY?

03:49.196 --> 03:51.064
BECAUSE HE'LL BE GONE
FOR HIS BIRTHDAY.

03:51.064 --> 03:52.065
CAN WE HAVE
A PARTY FOR HIM

03:52.065 --> 03:53.767
WHILE HE'S GONE?

03:53.767 --> 03:58.472
I HOPE YOU'RE SHOWERED
AND READY FOR SCHOOL.

04:00.474 --> 04:02.042
* I NEVER DREAMED THAT *

04:02.042 --> 04:06.814
* I WOULD LET HER GO *

04:11.118 --> 04:12.119
* AND I *

04:12.119 --> 04:13.654
SAM WRECKED
HIS CLOSET.

04:13.654 --> 04:19.527
* WILL GET WHAT I DESERVE *

04:20.994 --> 04:22.663
HEY! SPEEDY! GET!
[WHISTLES]

04:22.663 --> 04:24.998
SPEEDY!
GET OUTTA THERE!

04:24.998 --> 04:26.133
WAIT, NO! WAIT.

04:26.133 --> 04:28.001
STAY THERE.
GOOD BOY. RIGHT.

04:29.136 --> 04:30.137
COME TO DADDY.

04:30.137 --> 04:32.139
* OPEN THE CURTAINS *

04:32.139 --> 04:33.240
COME TO DADDY.

04:33.240 --> 04:34.542
* I SAID *

04:34.542 --> 04:39.146
* AND WHAT YOU WISH FOR
COULD COME TRUE *

04:39.146 --> 04:40.981
* YOU AREN'T
SURPRISED, LOVE *

04:40.981 --> 04:42.816
* ARE *

04:42.816 --> 04:43.817
COME HERE, GUSTER.

04:45.753 --> 04:46.687
* YOU? *

04:46.687 --> 04:49.256
[HONKS HORN]
[GUSTER BARKS]

04:49.256 --> 04:52.025
HAVE A NICE DAY.

04:52.025 --> 04:53.394
STAY.

04:53.394 --> 04:54.695
THIS HAS GOT TO STOP.

04:54.695 --> 04:57.164
HE ESCAPED.
NOW HE'S BACK IN.

04:57.164 --> 04:59.667
DOES IT GIVE YOU

04:59.667 --> 05:04.672
SOME SORT OF PERVERSE
PLEASURE TO EXPOSE YOUR PENIS

05:04.672 --> 05:07.307
IN FRONT OF
MY 16-YEAR-OLD DAUGHTER?

05:11.412 --> 05:13.781
MY EXPOSURE DOES NOT
FACE YOUR WINDOWS.

05:13.781 --> 05:15.849
GEORGE, THIS
IS THE THIRD TIME.

05:15.849 --> 05:18.051
THE PLUMBER'S
DUE OUT TOMORROW.

05:18.051 --> 05:19.186
WELL, YOU WILL JUST

05:19.186 --> 05:20.921
HAVE TO EXPLAIN THAT
TO THE POLICE.

05:20.921 --> 05:24.625
YOU WERE THE ONE NEIGHBOR
I COULD TOLERATE.

05:24.625 --> 05:27.461
[DOOR SLAMS,
CAR STARTS]

05:27.461 --> 05:29.963
COLEEN...

05:31.331 --> 05:33.333
JUST HOW FAR
OUT THAT WINDOW

05:33.333 --> 05:34.435
DID YOU HAVE
TO STICK YOUR HEAD

05:34.435 --> 05:36.404
TO BE ABLE
TO SEE MY DICK?

05:39.339 --> 05:40.774
I LIKE YOUR P.J.'s.

05:40.774 --> 05:43.544
[REVS MOTOR]

05:48.682 --> 05:50.451
I WISH YOU'D
TALK TO HIM.

05:50.451 --> 05:52.386
HE NEEDS A MAN.

05:52.386 --> 05:55.155
HIS FATHER'S A MAN.

05:55.155 --> 05:57.491
A MAN HE RESPECTS.

05:57.491 --> 05:58.892
Man: HE RESPECTS NOTHING.

05:58.892 --> 06:02.530
THANKS FOR TALKING
ABOUT ME BEHIND MY BACK.

06:02.530 --> 06:04.832
IT'S USEFUL IN COURT.

06:04.832 --> 06:07.034
ARE YOU WEARING
EYE MAKEUP?

06:07.034 --> 06:09.403
NO.

06:09.403 --> 06:11.872
TAKE IT OFF.

06:11.872 --> 06:15.609
IF I JUST WALK
OUT THE DOOR RIGHT NOW,

06:15.609 --> 06:18.145
WHO'S GONNA BE HERE TONIGHT
FOR THE FOLLOW THROUGH?

06:22.483 --> 06:24.051
HAVE A NICE FLIGHT.

06:28.021 --> 06:29.457
QUEER.

06:29.457 --> 06:31.625
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

06:31.625 --> 06:33.794
Boy: DAD SAID IT FIRST.

06:38.466 --> 06:40.734
I GET CHOCOLATE CAKE
FOR YOUR BIRTHDAY.

06:40.734 --> 06:42.570
GOOD. ARE YOUR HANDS CLEAN?

06:53.346 --> 06:55.115
Boy: THERE'S THE FREAK.

06:56.650 --> 06:58.652
* DON'T NEED NO ANYONE *

06:58.652 --> 07:00.454
* DON'T NEED NO ANYBODY *

07:00.454 --> 07:02.122
* TO TALK TO ME ABOUT *

07:02.122 --> 07:04.792
DUDE, NICE LOOK.

07:04.792 --> 07:07.628
I SAW YOUR DAD
THIS MORNING.

07:07.628 --> 07:10.263
Boy: HEY, JOSH,
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

07:10.263 --> 07:11.899
IS HE IN?

07:11.899 --> 07:14.968
BEEN THINKIN'
ABOUT THE JOB, MAN?

07:14.968 --> 07:16.537
NO.

07:16.537 --> 07:18.271
YEAH, FORGET HIM.

07:18.271 --> 07:20.340
2 HOURS A WEEK
FOR 300 CASH

07:20.340 --> 07:23.343
THE WHOLE SUMMER.
DO THE MATH.

07:23.343 --> 07:24.678
Boy: HE'S NOT
GONNA DO IT, JOSH.

07:24.678 --> 07:27.147
GUESS HE DOESN'T
HAVE IT IN HIM.

07:27.147 --> 07:28.448
THEY CONSIDER THIS

07:28.448 --> 07:30.818
A HATCHBACK
OR A STATION WAGON?

07:30.818 --> 07:32.252
[LAUGHS]

07:32.252 --> 07:33.554
Boy: LET'S GET
OUTTA HERE, DUDE.

07:34.955 --> 07:37.825
Josh: THINK ABOUT IT.
I'LL BE AROUND.

07:40.293 --> 07:43.430
[LAUGHS]
DUDE, I WAS IN TOTAL REM.

07:43.430 --> 07:45.065
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

07:45.065 --> 07:46.399
Receptionist:
BENSON, KIDDER ARCHITECTURE.

07:46.399 --> 07:47.601
CAN I HELP YOU?

07:47.601 --> 07:49.670
YES, SIR.

07:49.670 --> 07:52.540
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

07:56.009 --> 07:57.010
DONE?

07:57.010 --> 07:58.011
CLOSE TO DONE?

07:58.011 --> 07:59.680
I'M DOING THE GRASS.

07:59.680 --> 08:00.748
FUCK THE GRASS.

08:00.748 --> 08:02.550
BROOK BID OUT
THE BERLIN PLAZA.

08:02.550 --> 08:03.651
DID HE TELL YOU?

08:03.651 --> 08:06.353
I WAS GONNA START
THAT ON MONDAY.

08:06.353 --> 08:07.521
WELL, HE LIKES TO LOOK

08:07.521 --> 08:09.189
AT THE COMPUTER MODELS
BETTER, ANYWAY.

08:09.189 --> 08:10.858
YOU TAKE TOO LONG.

08:10.858 --> 08:12.526
UH, WHEN YOU'RE DONE
MOWING THE GRASS HERE,

08:12.526 --> 08:14.595
DO YOU MIND BRINGING
THE HOUSE UP TO MY OFFICE?

08:14.595 --> 08:15.596
I GOT A PRESENTATION
TO MAKE.

08:15.596 --> 08:17.931
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

08:17.931 --> 08:19.332
Receptionist: BENSON, KIDDER,
FINE, SILVER, AND ASSOCIATES.

08:19.332 --> 08:20.534
CAN I HELP YOU?

08:25.906 --> 08:27.407
[SIGHS]

08:27.407 --> 08:30.611
[MUSIC PLAYS]

08:38.284 --> 08:39.852
I WOULDN'T MAKE
A HABIT OF IT.

08:39.852 --> 08:42.289
* EVERY TIME I LOOK INSIDE *

08:42.289 --> 08:48.962
* THERE'S NOTHIN'
BUT AN EMPTY HEART *

08:52.800 --> 08:57.537
* AN EMPTY HEART *

09:07.447 --> 09:09.049
I COULD BE ANYONE.

09:09.049 --> 09:11.952
[SIGHS]

09:11.952 --> 09:13.654
THEN WHY
DO YOU STAY YOU?

09:13.654 --> 09:15.322
YOU SHOULD
LOCK YOUR DOOR.

09:15.322 --> 09:16.489
MMM, WELL,

09:16.489 --> 09:18.792
RING THE BELL BEFORE
YOU TRY THE DOOR.

09:21.528 --> 09:22.630
DID SAM
CALL TO TELL YOU

09:22.630 --> 09:23.964
HE WOULDN'T BE OVER
THIS WEEKEND?

09:23.964 --> 09:29.603
NO. WHY DID YOU LET HIM
PIERCE HIS CHIN?

09:31.905 --> 09:34.908
WHAT KIND OF A MOTHER
CAN'T STAND HER OWN SON?

09:40.547 --> 09:42.082
I DON'T KNOW.

09:50.724 --> 09:52.793
[KNOCKS]
SAM?

09:57.230 --> 09:58.799
SAM.

10:02.235 --> 10:05.372
WHY AREN'T YOU COMING
FOR THE WEEKEND?

10:09.977 --> 10:13.446
WHAT IS HE DOING? GEORGE?

10:13.446 --> 10:16.684
GEORGE, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

10:16.684 --> 10:17.785
HE DOESN'T ANSWER.

10:17.785 --> 10:18.919
HE NEVER ANSWERS.

10:18.919 --> 10:20.453
WHY DOES HE HAVE
A LOCK ON HIS DOOR?

10:20.453 --> 10:22.122
BECAUSE HE PUT
A LOCK ON IT.

10:22.122 --> 10:23.623
DO YOU REALLY
THINK I TOLD HIM

10:23.623 --> 10:25.325
HE COULD PUT
A HOLE IN HIS FACE?

10:25.325 --> 10:26.593
YOU JUST CLIMB UP THERE

10:26.593 --> 10:28.929
AND TELL HIM WHAT
HE CAN AND CAN'T DO.

10:28.929 --> 10:31.264
TAKE HIM FOR
THE SUMMER, OK?

10:31.264 --> 10:35.002
WHIP HIM INTO SHAPE.
MAKE HIM SMILE.

10:35.002 --> 10:38.205
LET HIM HATE YOU
FOR A WHILE.

10:38.205 --> 10:40.207
[MUSIC PLAYS]

10:46.279 --> 10:48.849
George: YOU NEED ALL
THE BRAIN CELLS YOU'VE GOT.

10:50.483 --> 10:52.352
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

10:52.352 --> 10:53.721
SAM.

10:53.721 --> 10:56.089
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

10:56.089 --> 10:57.224
GO AWAY.

11:03.831 --> 11:07.034
Robin: I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO ANYMORE.

11:07.034 --> 11:11.038
YOU TAKE HIM.
JUST TAKE HIM.

11:11.038 --> 11:13.240
YOU'RE SUCH
A GOOD FATHER.

11:21.681 --> 11:23.050
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING IN MY ROOM?

11:23.050 --> 11:24.852
I DIDN'T GO IN YOUR ROOM.

11:24.852 --> 11:27.721
I LOCKED THE DOOR.
GET OUT!

11:27.721 --> 11:28.922
[DOOR SLAMS]

11:28.922 --> 11:30.423
Sam: WHY, WHAT,
DO YOU THINK I'M STUPID?

11:30.423 --> 11:32.525
I LOCKED THE DOOR.
[CRASH]

11:32.525 --> 11:35.595
THIS IS MY ROOM!
[THUD]

11:35.595 --> 11:39.499
YOU HAVE NO RIGHTS HERE.
THIS IS MINE!

11:39.499 --> 11:41.769
THIS IS STUPID!
[THUD]

11:41.769 --> 11:43.403
WHY CAN'T
YOU ALL JUST DIE

11:43.403 --> 11:46.539
AND LEAVE ME ALONE?

11:46.539 --> 11:48.742
[CLANGING]

12:06.293 --> 12:08.528
Receptionist: BENSON, KIDDER,
FINE, SILVER, AND ASSOCIATES.

12:08.528 --> 12:09.763
CAN I HELP YOU, PLEASE?

12:09.763 --> 12:11.131
GEORGE, GOOD MORNING.

12:11.131 --> 12:12.465
UH, MR. BURKE WOULD LIKE
TO SEE YOU IN HIS OFFICE.

12:39.026 --> 12:41.628
GEORGE, COME ON IN.
HAVE A SEAT.

12:41.628 --> 12:43.964
ORANGE JUICE,
CROISSANT?

12:43.964 --> 12:46.066
NO, I'M GOOD.

12:46.066 --> 12:48.501
WHAT ARE YOU ON, GEORGE?

12:48.501 --> 12:50.237
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

12:50.237 --> 12:52.239
HOW MUCH WEIGHT
HAVE YOU LOST?

12:52.239 --> 12:55.708
OH, I DON'T KNOW.
UH, 5, 10 POUNDS.

12:55.708 --> 12:56.743
I HAVEN'T BEEN
VERY HUNGRY.

12:56.743 --> 12:59.112
HOW'S YOUR WIFE?

12:59.112 --> 13:02.883
WELL, UM, WHEN
WE DIVORCED A DECADE AGO

13:02.883 --> 13:06.186
SHE WAS VERY, VERY ANGRY.
NOW SHE'S JUST HOSTILE.

13:06.186 --> 13:07.720
RIGHT.

13:07.720 --> 13:09.156
I DID TELL YOU, DIDN'T I,

13:09.156 --> 13:11.791
THAT I WOULD BE READY TO START
THE BERLIN MODEL TODAY?

13:14.427 --> 13:17.998
OK. GEORGE, THIS IS--
THIS IS NOT ME.

13:17.998 --> 13:21.869
UH, WE CAN SHOW CLIENTS
ENDLESS OPTIONS.

13:21.869 --> 13:23.203
WE CAN CHANGE
ANYTHING, REALLY,

13:23.203 --> 13:25.138
IN A MATTER OF HOURS
ON THE COMPUTER,

13:25.138 --> 13:28.942
BUT, UH,
BUT YOU WON'T CHANGE.

13:33.146 --> 13:36.083
[CHUCKLES]
I'VE BEEN HERE 20 YEARS.

13:36.083 --> 13:40.888
MAYBE THAT'S--
MAYBE THAT'S TOO LONG.

13:40.888 --> 13:43.123
MAYBE?

13:43.123 --> 13:48.161
IT'S TOO LONG.
LISTEN...

13:48.161 --> 13:51.198
THEY DECIDED ON A WEEK
A YEAR SEVERANCE,

13:51.198 --> 13:54.301
BUT I GOT 'EM TO 26, OK?

13:54.301 --> 13:55.402
YOU CAN LEARN
ALL YOU NEED TO

13:55.402 --> 13:56.769
ON THE COMPUTER
LONG BEFORE THAT.

13:56.769 --> 13:57.770
YOU CAN MAYBE--
YOU CAN MAYBE EVEN

13:57.770 --> 14:00.273
FIND A JOB
CLOSER TO HOME.

14:02.775 --> 14:04.244
I HATE THIS JOB.

14:04.244 --> 14:06.079
AH, GEORGE, WHAT ARE
YOU TALKIN' ABOUT?

14:06.079 --> 14:07.780
YOU LOVE YOUR JOB.

14:07.780 --> 14:12.052
NOPE. FROM THE DAY
I STARTED TO TODAY...

14:12.052 --> 14:13.286
CAN'T STAND IT.

14:13.286 --> 14:15.755
WELL, GOOD.
THEN IT SOUNDS

14:15.755 --> 14:17.690
LIKE I'M DOIN'
YOU A FAVOR.

14:17.690 --> 14:20.060
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I, UH,

14:20.060 --> 14:21.828
I FEEL BETTER
ABOUT THIS.

14:21.828 --> 14:24.231
GOOD. I WAS
HOPING YOU WOULD.

14:24.231 --> 14:25.232
YEAH.

14:35.608 --> 14:36.977
UM...

14:38.578 --> 14:40.647
CAN I ASK YOU
ONE FAVOR?

14:40.647 --> 14:42.482
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YA?

14:42.482 --> 14:45.618
WELL, I BUILT MY FIRST
MODEL HERE WHEN I WAS 25.

14:45.618 --> 14:49.322
THERE MUST BE HUNDREDS
OF 'EM AROUND THE OFFICE.

14:49.322 --> 14:51.724
I WAS WONDERING
IF I MIGHT, YOU KNOW,

14:51.724 --> 14:53.260
PICK A FEW TO TAKE HOME?

14:53.260 --> 14:55.963
YOU KNOW, JUST THE ONES THAT
REALLY MEAN SOMETHING TO ME.

14:55.963 --> 15:00.167
WELL--WELL, UM, THOSE--

15:00.167 --> 15:01.834
THOSE--I MEAN, GEORGE,

15:01.834 --> 15:04.237
WE CAN'T REALLY
KEEP OUR WORK.

15:04.237 --> 15:07.307
I--I CAN MAYBE ASK THEM
IF YOU COULD CHOOSE ONE,

15:07.307 --> 15:10.577
BUT THEY'RE
A PART OF THE FIRM.

15:10.577 --> 15:12.245
LOOK, WHY DON'T YOU

15:12.245 --> 15:13.713
GO OUT THERE
AND LOOK THEM OVER,

15:13.713 --> 15:16.183
EVERY SINGLE
ONE OF THEM, OK?

15:16.183 --> 15:17.917
YOU PICK THE ONE
YOU LIKE THE BEST.

15:17.917 --> 15:19.519
TAKE IT WITH YOU.

15:19.519 --> 15:23.890
NOW, RUN IT BY ME FIRST,
JUST IN CASE, YOU KNOW.

15:23.890 --> 15:25.658
I'M SURE IT'LL BE OK.

16:34.594 --> 16:36.529
[WOMEN SCREAM]

16:45.205 --> 16:46.973
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

16:46.973 --> 16:48.641
OH, MAN!
OH, NO!

17:01.854 --> 17:04.656
Woman: GEORGE, GEORGE.

17:04.656 --> 17:07.060
GEORGE, MR. BURKE
WOULD LIKE TO SEE YOU...

17:07.060 --> 17:08.127
FINE.

17:08.127 --> 17:09.096
IN HIS OFFICE,
WHEN YOU'RE ABLE.

17:09.096 --> 17:10.530
SURE.

17:13.366 --> 17:15.268
I'LL KEEP THIS ONE,
IF THAT'S ALL RIGHT WITH YOU.

17:15.268 --> 17:18.204
YOU'RE A GREAT ARCHITECT
AND A MISERABLE HUMAN BEING.

17:18.204 --> 17:19.205
THAT'S MINE.

17:19.205 --> 17:21.708
NO! GEORGE! OH, SHIT!

17:21.708 --> 17:23.476
SHIT!

17:23.476 --> 17:25.112
YOU'RE NOT EVEN
A FUCKIN' ARCHITECT,

17:25.112 --> 17:26.979
AND YOU'RE A MISERABLE
HUMAN BEING.

17:26.979 --> 17:30.183
YOU'RE RIGHT.
YOU WIN.

17:47.667 --> 17:49.736
Receptionist: WHOA!

17:49.736 --> 17:51.070
GEORGE?

17:51.070 --> 17:52.905
SIR, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

17:52.905 --> 17:54.374
GEORGE?
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

17:54.374 --> 17:55.942
GEORGE,
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

17:55.942 --> 17:57.610
Woman: IS THERE A DOCTOR--

17:57.610 --> 17:59.212
SOMEONE CALL 911.

19:16.623 --> 19:19.292
THAT TOOK CARE
OF THE PAIN?

19:19.292 --> 19:22.229
George: OH,
I COULD KISS YOU.

19:22.229 --> 19:26.966
OH. OH.

19:26.966 --> 19:31.838
NO FOOD. OH.

19:31.838 --> 19:33.440
I'M PAINLESS.

19:38.044 --> 19:39.145
WHAT WOULD YOU DO

19:39.145 --> 19:42.382
IF YOU HAD 3 OR 4
MONTHS TO LIVE?

19:42.382 --> 19:45.252
UM, I'D EAT
A LOT OF RED MEAT.

19:45.252 --> 19:47.019
[LAUGHS]

19:47.019 --> 19:49.689
GOOD FOR YOU.

19:49.689 --> 19:51.190
WHAT WOULD YOU DO?

19:53.125 --> 19:55.328
BUILD A HOUSE.

19:55.328 --> 19:56.729
YEAH, WHAT KIND OF HOUSE?

19:59.466 --> 20:02.068
YOU KNOW WHAT
MORTISE AND TENON IS?

20:02.068 --> 20:04.404
MM-MMM.

20:04.404 --> 20:07.206
I'VE GOT EVERY
PART OF IT READY.

20:07.206 --> 20:08.708
IT'S LIKE
A JIGSAW PUZZLE,

20:08.708 --> 20:12.379
ALL IN PIECES NOW
WAITING TO MAKE SENSE.

20:12.379 --> 20:13.813
I'VE BEEN THROUGH
DESIGN REVIEW,

20:13.813 --> 20:16.916
THE PLANNING COMMISSION,
THE CITY COUNCIL...

20:22.789 --> 20:23.790
NO ONE'S REALLY SAID

20:23.790 --> 20:25.858
THAT 4 MONTHS IS ALL
YOU HAVE, HAVE THEY?

20:25.858 --> 20:29.296
NOBODY'S EVEN, UH...

20:29.296 --> 20:32.164
PRETENDED
TO OFFER TREATMENT.

20:32.164 --> 20:34.867
SO YOU TELL ME,
WHY WOULD YOU START

20:34.867 --> 20:39.238
UH, EATING RED MEAT?

20:39.238 --> 20:42.309
CAN YOU BUILD A HOUSE
IN 4 MONTHS?

20:42.309 --> 20:44.611
I CAN DIE TRYING.

20:47.747 --> 20:48.648
GOOD FOR YOU.

20:48.648 --> 20:53.286
I HAVE NOT BEEN
TOUCHED IN YEARS.

20:53.286 --> 20:56.155
REALLY?

20:56.155 --> 20:58.625
NO, I MEAN,
NOT A FRIEND...

20:58.625 --> 21:00.527
YOUR--YOUR MOTHER?
I MEAN...

21:00.527 --> 21:01.794
PEOPLE HAVE TO BE TOUCHED.

21:01.794 --> 21:04.697
EVERYONE GETS TOUCHED
BY SOMEBODY THEY LOVE.

21:04.697 --> 21:07.300
I KNOW.

21:07.300 --> 21:09.802
IT'S WEIRD, ISN'T IT?

21:09.802 --> 21:14.040
I KNOW MY SON,
WHEN HE WAS YOUNGER...

21:14.040 --> 21:17.977
10 OR 11 EVEN, HE, UH,

21:17.977 --> 21:20.613
USED TO RUN UP AND THROW
HIS ARMS AROUND ME.

22:15.001 --> 22:17.770
MMM.

22:17.770 --> 22:21.441
I'M SORRY.

22:27.780 --> 22:30.116
I'M SCARED.

22:43.930 --> 22:45.432
[HONKS HORN]

22:45.432 --> 22:49.335
GEORGE!
[HONK HONK]

22:49.335 --> 22:51.070
GEORGE!

22:59.211 --> 23:00.847
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

23:00.847 --> 23:02.582
I CALLED EVERYONE
EVERYWHERE.

23:02.582 --> 23:04.083
YOU JUST VANISHED.

23:04.083 --> 23:05.284
YOU COULD BE DEAD.

23:05.284 --> 23:06.285
LOUD TODAY.

23:06.285 --> 23:07.487
YOU ARE INCONSIDERATE,

23:07.487 --> 23:10.757
AND ABSOLUTELY
DEVOID OF EMOTION.

23:10.757 --> 23:14.427
YOU'RE THE MOST BEAUTIFUL
WOMAN I HAVE EVER KNOWN.

23:14.427 --> 23:15.562
WHAT?

23:15.562 --> 23:17.196
I DON'T MEAN
JUST PHYSICALLY,

23:17.196 --> 23:18.965
EVEN YOUR ANGER
IS PERFECT.

23:18.965 --> 23:21.200
AND WHERE HAVE
YOU BEEN FOR A WEEK?

23:21.200 --> 23:23.202
4 DAYS.

23:23.202 --> 23:26.205
I HAVE TO TALK TO YOU.

23:26.205 --> 23:27.406
WHY WOULD THEY
TOW YOUR TRUCK?

23:27.406 --> 23:31.310
I'M GONNA
TEAR DOWN THE SHACK

23:31.310 --> 23:32.311
AND BUILD THE HOUSE.

23:32.311 --> 23:34.313
OH...

23:34.313 --> 23:36.015
YOU'VE BEEN SAYING
THAT FOR 20 YEARS.

23:36.015 --> 23:38.751
WHILE WE WERE
DATING YOU SAID IT.

23:38.751 --> 23:40.787
WELL, NOW THERE'S
NOTHING TO STOP ME.

23:40.787 --> 23:41.621
OH, MONEY?

23:41.621 --> 23:44.491
SEVERANCE PAY,
AND I'M GONNA

23:44.491 --> 23:46.325
CASH IN MY LIFE
INSURANCE POLICY.

23:46.325 --> 23:48.561
WHERE WILL YOU LIVE?

23:48.561 --> 23:50.763
IN THE GARAGE.

23:50.763 --> 23:53.533
LOOK, I WASN'T SERIOUS
ABOUT YOU TAKING SAM,

23:53.533 --> 23:54.767
SO YOU DON'T HAVE
TO GET INTO

23:54.767 --> 23:57.403
ANY ACTUAL CONSTRUCTION
TO GET OUT OF IT.

23:57.403 --> 23:59.405
WHEN DOES SCHOOL LET OUT?

23:59.405 --> 24:01.974
FRIDAY. TOMORROW.

24:01.974 --> 24:03.342
OH, GOD.

24:03.342 --> 24:05.845
I HATE THE THOUGHT
OF HIM HOME ALL DAY.

24:05.845 --> 24:08.247
I'LL BE BY SATURDAY
TO PICK HIM UP.

24:08.247 --> 24:09.549
HE DOESN'T
WANNA SPEND

24:09.549 --> 24:11.350
THE WEEKENDS
WITH YOU ANYMORE.

24:11.350 --> 24:14.921
NOT FOR THE WEEKEND,
FOR THE SUMMER.

24:14.921 --> 24:16.956
ONE OF YOU
WOULD END UP DEAD.

24:16.956 --> 24:17.857
YEAH, BUT AT LEAST

24:17.857 --> 24:19.358
WE'D HAVE A HOUSE
TO SHOW FOR IT.

24:19.358 --> 24:22.094
FORGET IT, REALLY.
I'LL SURVIVE.

24:24.230 --> 24:25.632
I WANT HIM WITH ME.

24:25.632 --> 24:27.333
NO, YOU DON'T.
TRUST ME.

24:27.333 --> 24:31.470
I WANT SAM
FOR THE SUMMER.

24:31.470 --> 24:33.039
OK.

24:36.943 --> 24:39.378
AAH! JESUS.

24:39.378 --> 24:40.880
WELL, I AM MARRIED.

24:40.880 --> 24:44.383
OK.

24:44.383 --> 24:45.585
HMM.

24:47.419 --> 24:49.522
THE WHOLE SUMMER, SAM.
PARTY IN TAHOE.

24:49.522 --> 24:50.523
I DON'T KNOW, COREY.

24:50.523 --> 24:51.791
LET ME THINK
ABOUT IT, OK?

24:51.791 --> 24:53.626
ALL WE GOTTA DO IS SAND
AND PAINT THE CABIN.

24:53.626 --> 24:55.194
MY DAD IS GONNA
LET ME USE HIS BOAT.

24:55.194 --> 24:57.296
MY CHARM'S GONNA
LET ME USE MY ROD,

24:57.296 --> 24:58.531
AND YOU KNOW
THAT INCA VILLAGE

24:58.531 --> 25:00.600
IS THE PLACE TO HOOK UP
WITH SOME HUMP.

25:00.600 --> 25:01.668
OK, I'LL ASK.

25:01.668 --> 25:02.669
ALL RIGHT.
I'M JUST SAYIN'

25:02.669 --> 25:03.803
IT BEATS
LETTIN' TOWN FOLK

25:03.803 --> 25:06.806
GO DOWN ON YOU
FOR THE SUMMER.

25:06.806 --> 25:08.641
YO, I HAVEN'T
DONE ANYTHING.

25:08.641 --> 25:10.342
UH, I KNOW
WHAT THE DEAL IS.

25:10.342 --> 25:11.911
JOSH IS A PIMP.
I'M NOT STUPID.

25:11.911 --> 25:13.546
OBVIOUSLY, YOU DON'T
KNOW WHAT THE DEAL IS

25:13.546 --> 25:15.281
BECAUSE THERE
IS NO FUCKING DEAL.

25:17.750 --> 25:19.251
LIGHTEN UP, DUDE.

25:36.035 --> 25:37.970
[BELL RINGS]

25:43.876 --> 25:45.077
GOOD MORNING,
MR. GEORGE.

25:45.077 --> 25:45.945
HI.

25:45.945 --> 25:48.080
MRS. KIMBERLY'S
IN THE BACKYARD.

25:48.080 --> 25:50.049
AND, UH?

25:50.049 --> 25:51.684
PACKING.

25:54.420 --> 25:55.788
GOOD.

25:57.189 --> 26:00.426
* SOME OF THEM
WANT TO USE YOU *

26:00.426 --> 26:02.194
George: SAM!

26:02.194 --> 26:07.634
* SOME OF THEM
WANNA GET USED BY YOU *

26:07.634 --> 26:11.503
* SOME OF THEM WANT
TO ABUSE YOU *

26:11.503 --> 26:12.705
ALMOST READY?

26:12.705 --> 26:18.878
* SOME OF THEM
WANT TO BE ABUSED *

26:18.878 --> 26:20.647
YOU MIND TURNING THIS DOWN?

26:23.482 --> 26:24.984
* I'M GONNA USE YOU *

26:24.984 --> 26:26.252
IT WON'T BE
ALL WORK, YOU KNOW.

26:26.252 --> 26:28.120
* AND ABUSE YOU *

26:28.120 --> 26:30.923
* I'M GONNA
KNOW WHAT'S INSIDE... *

26:30.923 --> 26:35.094
IT WON'T
BE ALL WORK!

26:35.094 --> 26:35.895
[MUSIC STOPS]

26:35.895 --> 26:37.864
I HEARD YOU ALREADY.

26:37.864 --> 26:41.233
AND YOUR MOM AND THE BOYS
CAN COME BY ANY TIME.

26:41.233 --> 26:43.569
WHAT, TO CHECK UP ON ME?

26:43.569 --> 26:45.404
I'LL BE THERE
TO CHECK UP ON YOU.

26:45.404 --> 26:46.906
WHY WOULD YOU BE THERE?

26:46.906 --> 26:48.941
WELL, I LIVE THERE.

26:48.941 --> 26:52.544
YOU LIVE IN COREY'S
PARENTS' CABIN IN TAHOE?

26:52.544 --> 26:54.546
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

26:54.546 --> 26:56.048
WHO'S COREY?

26:56.048 --> 26:57.950
COREY'S MY FRIEND. I'M GOIN'
TO SPEND THE SUMMER, OK?

26:57.950 --> 26:59.218
NO, YOU'RE NOT
GOIN' ANYWHERE.

26:59.218 --> 27:01.287
YOU'RE SPENDING
THE SUMMER WITH ME.

27:01.287 --> 27:02.521
George: ROBIN!
SHIT!

27:02.521 --> 27:03.622
NO FUCKIN' WAY!

27:03.622 --> 27:04.957
ROBIN, DID YOU TELL SAM

27:04.957 --> 27:06.358
HE WAS SPENDING
THE SUMMER WITH ME?

27:06.358 --> 27:07.894
WHAT WAS
I SUPPOSED TO DO?

27:07.894 --> 27:09.495
I TRIED TO CALL.
YOUR PHONE ISN'T WORKING.

27:09.495 --> 27:10.697
I DON'T HAVE
A PHONE ANYMORE.

27:10.697 --> 27:11.898
WHO ARE YOU, ANYWAY?

27:11.898 --> 27:13.365
I DON'T EVEN KNOW YOU.

27:13.365 --> 27:14.767
YOU'LL KNOW ME BY
THE TIME WE'RE THROUGH.

27:14.767 --> 27:16.736
I'M NOT GOING.

27:16.736 --> 27:18.637
I'LL GET YOUR BAG.

27:20.807 --> 27:21.974
WOULD YOU TELL HIM
THAT I'M NOT GOING?

27:21.974 --> 27:24.911
YOU ALREADY
PROMISED ME.

27:24.911 --> 27:26.245
GEORGE, I DID SAY
HE COULD GO.

27:26.245 --> 27:27.246
IS THIS EVERYTHING?

27:27.246 --> 27:29.581
MOM, PLEASE TELL HIM.

27:29.581 --> 27:31.851
GEORGE. UH...

27:31.851 --> 27:35.254
HE IS NOT SPENDING
THE ENTIRE SUMMER

27:35.254 --> 27:36.989
WITH SOME KID IN TAHOE.

27:36.989 --> 27:39.926
HE CAN HATE ME.
YOU CAN HATE ME.

27:39.926 --> 27:42.094
HE CAN TRY TO KILL ME
WHILE I'M SLEEPING.

27:42.094 --> 27:43.162
I DON'T CARE.

27:43.162 --> 27:46.465
SAM IS SPENDING
THE SUMMER WITH ME, OK?

27:46.465 --> 27:48.134
HE'S MY SON. HE'S 16.

27:48.134 --> 27:49.435
THAT'S IT!

27:49.435 --> 27:50.669
Boy: CAN I HATE YOU, TOO?

27:52.671 --> 27:53.940
YOU CAN DO
ANYTHING YOU WANT.

27:53.940 --> 27:54.941
GO GET
IN THE TRUCK.

27:54.941 --> 27:57.309
Sam: THEN GO
FUCK YOURSELF!

27:58.811 --> 28:01.748
SAM. SAM. LISTEN TO ME.

28:01.748 --> 28:04.150
LISTEN!

28:04.150 --> 28:06.786
I WANT THAT THING
OUT OF YOUR CHIN, OK?

28:06.786 --> 28:08.454
IF YOU GOT NIPPLE RINGS
AND NAVEL RINGS,

28:08.454 --> 28:09.688
THOSE COME OUT, TOO,

28:09.688 --> 28:11.390
AND THERE'S NO MAKEUP
IN MY HOUSE.

28:11.390 --> 28:15.862
NO GLUE SNIFFING, HUFFING,
NO PILLS, NO GRASS.

28:15.862 --> 28:17.930
YOU'VE WORN OUT YOUR WELCOME
AT THIS HOUSE, SAM.

28:17.930 --> 28:20.532
THIS MAY WELL BE THE WORST
SUMMER OF YOUR ENTIRE LIFE,

28:20.532 --> 28:21.768
BUT YOU'VE EARNED IT.

28:21.768 --> 28:23.402
NOW, GO PICK UP
THE SUITCASE,

28:23.402 --> 28:25.137
AND GET IN THE TRUCK NOW.

28:28.875 --> 28:31.610
I'LL HATE YOU FOR
THE REST OF MY LIFE.

28:31.610 --> 28:33.479
BOY, YOU CAN'T EVEN
BEGIN TO KNOW

28:33.479 --> 28:34.580
HOW MUCH I HATE
MY FATHER.

28:34.580 --> 28:36.382
THINK OF IT AS
A FAMILY TRADITION.

28:49.929 --> 28:51.330
YOU LIKE GARLIC?

28:51.330 --> 28:53.900
YOU LIKE GARLIC BREAD?

28:53.900 --> 28:56.335
DO YOU LIKE GARLIC BREAD?

29:16.455 --> 29:18.757
THINKING OF JUMPING?

29:18.757 --> 29:21.360
PUSHING.

29:21.360 --> 29:23.729
WELL, DON'T JUMP TILL
YOU HEAR THE WAVE

29:23.729 --> 29:26.698
CRASH AGAINST THE CLIFF.

29:26.698 --> 29:29.435
THE WATER'LL
TAKE YOU OUT. LET IT.

29:29.435 --> 29:32.404
FIRST TIME I DID IT,

29:32.404 --> 29:33.840
YOUNGER THAN YOU,

29:33.840 --> 29:35.875
I THOUGHT
I'D BREAK MY NECK

29:35.875 --> 29:39.778
AND JUST SORT OF FLOAT
OUT TO CATALINA.

29:39.778 --> 29:43.282
YOU DON'T ALWAYS GET
WHAT YOU WISH FOR, SAM.

29:52.491 --> 29:55.594
YAAAAAAAAAH!

29:55.594 --> 29:57.729
Sam: SHIT.

29:57.729 --> 30:00.199
HELLO?

30:00.199 --> 30:02.334
HELLO?

30:02.334 --> 30:03.469
UHH.

30:05.872 --> 30:08.340
OH, MY GOD.

30:10.442 --> 30:12.311
WHOO-HOO-HOO!

30:14.480 --> 30:16.883
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.

30:18.484 --> 30:21.120
ARE YOU TOTALLY INSANE?!

30:21.120 --> 30:25.424
HA! YEAH! AH HA HA!

30:25.424 --> 30:26.425
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS.

30:26.425 --> 30:29.896
I GOT A TOTAL WACKO
FOR A FATHER.

30:29.896 --> 30:31.763
George: I ALMOST SAW
CATALINA!

30:31.763 --> 30:34.066
HA HA HA HA HA HA!

30:34.066 --> 30:37.036
AH HA HA HA HA!

30:37.036 --> 30:38.905
WHAT HAVE YOU GOTTEN
ALL OVER YOURSELF?

30:38.905 --> 30:40.639
WHAT IS THIS?
IS THIS PASTA SAUCE?

30:40.639 --> 30:42.774
YOU CRAZY DOG, GUSTER.

30:42.774 --> 30:44.110
COME HERE, LOOK IT.

30:44.110 --> 30:46.045
YOU'RE CRAZY,
YOU KNOW THIS?

30:46.045 --> 30:49.248
DO YOU KNOW THIS?
HEH HEH.

30:51.350 --> 30:52.451
HEY.

30:52.451 --> 30:53.452
HI.

30:53.452 --> 30:55.621
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

30:55.621 --> 30:56.923
UH, THEY'RE TRYING

30:56.923 --> 30:58.224
TO MAKE ME SPEND
THE SUMMER HERE,

30:58.224 --> 31:00.459
BUT I'M LEAVING
IN THE MORNING.

31:00.459 --> 31:02.228
OH. WHERE TO?

31:02.228 --> 31:05.231
I'M SUPPOSED
TO BE IN TAHOE.

31:05.231 --> 31:07.499
WELL, I GUESS IF YOU STAY,

31:07.499 --> 31:09.201
I'LL SEE YOU AROUND?

31:10.769 --> 31:13.772
YOU SHOULD STAY.

31:13.772 --> 31:15.874
WHERE'S YOUR DAD?

31:20.980 --> 31:23.916
HE JUMPED
INTO THE OCEAN.

31:25.985 --> 31:28.420
WELL, TELL HIM I SAY HELLO.

31:37.429 --> 31:41.900
[SINISTER LAUGHTER]

31:44.937 --> 31:46.905
PLEASE, GOD.

31:46.905 --> 31:48.807
THIS...

31:48.807 --> 31:50.076
IS GOD.

31:51.910 --> 31:53.512
AAAAAH!

31:53.512 --> 31:55.114
HA HA HA HA HA!

31:57.016 --> 32:01.253
I'M NOT TAKING A DUMP
WITH YOU IN HERE.

32:01.253 --> 32:03.855
MY BROTHERS SAY THAT
IT'S THE WORST SMELL

32:03.855 --> 32:06.392
THEY'VE EVER SMELLED.

32:13.399 --> 32:15.467
WHICH SIDE OF THE BED
DO YOU WANT?

32:15.467 --> 32:16.635
I'M NOT--

32:16.635 --> 32:17.836
JUST KIDDING.

32:17.836 --> 32:19.938
THE SOFA'S A PULLOUT.

32:20.973 --> 32:22.308
JEEZ.

32:22.308 --> 32:23.475
YOU KNOW,

32:23.475 --> 32:26.045
I THINK YOU HAVE
TO HAVE A DOOR

32:26.045 --> 32:30.049
BETWEEN WHERE YOU COOK
AND WHERE YOU CRAP.

32:30.049 --> 32:32.618
EVEN IN THE BUSH,
TRIBAL PEOPLE ARE LIKE THAT.

32:32.618 --> 32:35.087
THEY HAVE A PLACE FOR BOTH.

32:35.087 --> 32:37.489
PROBABLY, YOU KNOW,
IT'S--IT'S LIKE A LAW.

32:38.724 --> 32:40.292
HMM.

32:40.292 --> 32:41.627
GOD!

32:41.627 --> 32:44.430
PROBABLY IN THE BIBLE.

32:44.430 --> 32:47.266
IT'S AT LEAST
A BUILDING CODE VIOLATION.

32:50.969 --> 32:52.638
GOOD NIGHT.

32:52.638 --> 32:56.175
I HAVE TO TAKE A DUMP.

33:13.092 --> 33:14.926
HELP ME, PLEASE!

33:14.926 --> 33:16.828
HELP ME!

33:16.828 --> 33:19.865
AAAH!

33:19.865 --> 33:21.667
TINA!

33:42.654 --> 33:44.690
ARE YOU WEARING SUNSCREEN?

33:47.259 --> 33:49.361
ARE YOU WEARING
SUNSCREEN?

33:54.166 --> 33:56.168
I WONDER WHERE
HE'S LIVING.

33:56.168 --> 33:57.436
ABOUT TIME.

33:57.436 --> 34:00.172
THEY'RE FINALLY
TEARING DOWN THIS--

34:00.172 --> 34:02.074
THIS PILE OF JUNK.
YEAH.

34:02.074 --> 34:03.842
OH.

34:03.842 --> 34:05.043
HEY, GEORGE.
GEORGE.

34:05.043 --> 34:07.413
BARBARA, TOM.

34:09.447 --> 34:11.449
GUESS HOW MANY
LOW-INCOME APARTMENTS

34:11.449 --> 34:14.018
THE CITY APPROVED
FOR THIS LOT.

34:14.018 --> 34:15.254
BALLPARK FIGURE.

34:15.254 --> 34:16.922
NO, NO. NOT TODAY.

34:16.922 --> 34:18.424
YOU KNOW,
THERE WAS ALSO SOME TALK

34:18.424 --> 34:19.725
ABOUT A DRUG REHAB CENTER.

34:19.725 --> 34:20.826
JERK.

34:23.929 --> 34:25.496
SAM.

34:30.768 --> 34:32.971
SAM.

34:32.971 --> 34:34.806
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
DON'T TOUCH ME.

34:34.806 --> 34:36.242
I WARNED YOU YESTERDAY.

34:36.242 --> 34:38.444
YOU CAN'T TOUCH ME.

34:38.444 --> 34:39.545
HEY.

34:39.545 --> 34:41.380
YOU STAYED.

34:43.382 --> 34:44.983
RUB HIM DOWN,
WILL YOU, ALYSSA?

34:44.983 --> 34:46.485
[LAUGHS]

34:53.159 --> 34:54.560
HE'S INSANE.

34:54.560 --> 34:58.164
YOU LOOK BETTER
WITHOUT MAKEUP.

34:58.164 --> 35:00.466
I CAN'T EVEN
TAKE A SHOWER.

35:00.466 --> 35:02.801
COME OVER TO MY HOUSE
WHENEVER YOU WANT.

35:02.801 --> 35:04.470
I'LL TELL MY MOM.

35:04.470 --> 35:08.207
WELL, I MIGHT NOT
EVEN STAY ANYWAY.

35:08.207 --> 35:10.108
WELL, I'LL GET YOUR BACK.

35:10.108 --> 35:11.443
NO, THAT'S OK.
THANKS.

35:11.443 --> 35:13.679
HAVE YOU EVER HAD ANYONE
BESIDES YOUR MOM OR DAD

35:13.679 --> 35:15.781
PUT IT ON FOR YOU?

35:15.781 --> 35:18.016
IT'S, UH, IT'S WEIRD
HOW DIFFERENT IT IS.

35:18.016 --> 35:20.819
TURN AROUND.
JUST LAY DOWN.

35:20.819 --> 35:22.988
DO YOU REMEMBER ME

35:22.988 --> 35:26.124
FROM WHEN
YOU LIVED HERE BEFORE?

35:26.124 --> 35:27.926
YEAH.

35:27.926 --> 35:29.328
SO, I'VE DECIDED THAT

35:29.328 --> 35:32.431
I'M NOT GONNA SHAVE MY LEGS
OR MY PITS THIS SUMMER.

35:32.431 --> 35:33.465
YEAH?

35:33.465 --> 35:34.833
I MEAN, PAULA COLE
ISN'T A VERTICAL KISSER.

35:34.833 --> 35:37.636
REALLY?

35:37.636 --> 35:41.207
SO, YOUR DAD'S REALLY
GONNA BUILD HIS HOUSE, HUH?

35:41.207 --> 35:42.241
I DON'T KNOW.

35:42.241 --> 35:44.776
YOU KNOW YOUR DAD
DATED MY MOM

35:44.776 --> 35:46.645
AFTER HER DIVORCE.

35:46.645 --> 35:47.513
REALLY?

35:47.513 --> 35:49.581
YEAH, I WANTED HIM
TO MARRY HER.

35:51.049 --> 35:52.984
WHY?

35:52.984 --> 35:53.985
[BOTH LAUGH]

35:53.985 --> 35:55.120
TURN OVER.

35:55.120 --> 35:56.722
[CAR HORN HONKS]

35:59.258 --> 36:00.926
HEY, UM,

36:00.926 --> 36:02.761
JOSH AND I ARE ACTUALLY
GOING TO SOUTH COAST,

36:02.761 --> 36:06.332
IF YOU WANT A RIDE.
MAYBE SEE A MOVIE?

36:06.332 --> 36:07.399
NO, THANKS.

36:07.399 --> 36:08.600
[CAR HORN HONKS]

36:08.600 --> 36:10.869
ALL RIGHT. WELL,
DON'T FORGET YOUR FRONT.

36:10.869 --> 36:12.704
I'LL SEE YOU AROUND.

36:21.913 --> 36:24.750
PRETTY, ISN'T SHE?

36:25.951 --> 36:27.819
FOR A GIRL.

36:37.463 --> 36:39.565
FEEL FREE TO PITCH IN
ANYTIME.

36:44.035 --> 36:45.604
* JUST THINK ABOUT IT *

36:45.604 --> 36:47.806
* LATELY
I'VE BEEN SKEPTICAL *

36:47.806 --> 36:50.442
* SILENT WHEN I WOULD
USED TO SPEAK *

36:50.442 --> 36:52.511
* DISTANCE
FROM ALL AROUND ME *

36:52.511 --> 36:54.980
* WHO WITNESS ME FAIL
AND BECOME WEAK *

36:54.980 --> 36:56.648
* LIFE IS OVERWHELMING *

36:56.648 --> 36:59.418
* HEAVY IS THE HEAD
THAT WEARS THE CROWN *

36:59.418 --> 37:02.488
* I'D LOVE TO BE THE ONE TO
DISAPPOINT YOU *

37:02.488 --> 37:04.155
* WHEN I DON'T FALL DOWN *

37:04.155 --> 37:06.392
* BUT YOU MIGHT
NEED MY HAND WHEN *

37:06.392 --> 37:08.727
* FALLING IN YOUR HOLE *

37:08.727 --> 37:11.196
* YOUR DISPOSITION
I'LL REMEMBER *

37:11.196 --> 37:13.299
* WHEN I'M LETTING GO *

37:13.299 --> 37:15.701
* YOU *

37:15.701 --> 37:16.935
* AND ME *

37:16.935 --> 37:20.306
* WE'RE THROUGH *

37:20.306 --> 37:27.379
* AND REARRANGED *

37:36.254 --> 37:38.357
SAM, DO YOU EVER, UM,

37:38.357 --> 37:40.392
GET, LIKE,
THE SLIGHTEST INKLING

37:40.392 --> 37:41.693
THAT YOU MIGHT WANT
TO HELP ME

37:41.693 --> 37:45.096
INSTEAD OF DOING
ABSOLUTELY NOTHING?

37:45.096 --> 37:47.499
HERE.

37:50.101 --> 37:51.202
I HATE TURKEY.

37:51.202 --> 37:54.005
[SIGHS]
NO, YOU DON'T.

37:54.005 --> 37:55.206
IF I SAY I DO,

37:55.206 --> 37:57.909
I DO.

37:57.909 --> 37:58.877
PLEASE,

37:58.877 --> 38:02.581
TAKE THAT THUMBTACK
OUT OF YOUR FACE.

38:02.581 --> 38:04.750
LET ME--LET ME JUST
GET IT OUT.

38:04.750 --> 38:05.551
WHY?
COME ON.

38:05.551 --> 38:07.519
WHY?
IT BUGS ME.

38:07.519 --> 38:09.054
YOU SNORE AT NIGHT.

38:09.054 --> 38:11.156
THAT REALLY BUGS ME.

38:11.156 --> 38:13.425
CAN I TAKE YOU OUT?

38:19.064 --> 38:20.298
YOU KNOW,

38:20.298 --> 38:22.267
YOUR BROTHERS ARE RIGHT
ABOUT THAT SMELL.

38:22.267 --> 38:24.135
THAT WAS THE MOST
GOD-AWFUL THING

38:24.135 --> 38:25.771
I'VE EVER HAD
MY NOSE AROUND.

38:25.771 --> 38:26.772
TOLD YOU.

38:26.772 --> 38:27.806
IT'S TOXIC.

38:27.806 --> 38:28.707
HEY.

38:28.707 --> 38:30.409
I THOUGHT YOU GUYS
MIGHT BE HUNGRY.

38:30.409 --> 38:31.543
WE'RE FINE.

38:31.543 --> 38:33.044
TURKEY SANDWICHES.

38:33.044 --> 38:35.447
OH, WELL,
FOR LATER, THEN.

38:39.351 --> 38:40.986
OH.

38:40.986 --> 38:42.320
WOW.

38:44.089 --> 38:45.957
MAKES ME SAD.

38:45.957 --> 38:48.026
WHY?

38:48.026 --> 38:49.461
WE USED TO LIVE HERE.

38:49.461 --> 38:52.330
YEAH, YOU HATED 4 OUT OF
THE 5 YEARS THAT YOU DID.

38:52.330 --> 38:55.000
I WAS HERE 6 YEARS,

38:55.000 --> 38:56.368
AND I ONLY HATED 2.

38:56.368 --> 38:59.104
WHICH 2?

38:59.104 --> 39:01.673
THE FIRST AND THE LAST.

39:03.241 --> 39:05.611
I DON'T EVEN LIKE
TURKEY SANDWICHES.

39:05.611 --> 39:07.312
WHAT'S, UH,
WHAT'S THIS PIZZA?

39:07.312 --> 39:09.581
SAM'S FAVORITE.

39:09.581 --> 39:11.517
SURE YOU DON'T WANT ANY?

39:11.517 --> 39:13.084
[DOG BARKS]

39:15.454 --> 39:17.155
GEORGE,
YOU'RE TOO THIN,

39:17.155 --> 39:19.925
FROM WHAT YOU
USED TO BE ANYWAY.

39:21.860 --> 39:24.496
WHY THE FIRST
AND THE LAST?

39:24.496 --> 39:26.865
THE FIRST BECAUSE I WASN'T SURE
YOU REALLY LOVED ME,

39:26.865 --> 39:32.438
AND THE LAST BECAUSE I WASN'T
SURE I REALLY LOVED YOU.

39:34.372 --> 39:36.207
I WAS UP ON THAT
ROOF THIS MORNING,

39:36.207 --> 39:37.943
TEARING IT DOWN.

39:37.943 --> 39:38.744
IT STRUCK ME,

39:38.744 --> 39:41.212
STRONG AS ANYTHING
EVER HAS.

39:41.212 --> 39:44.616
I'M HAPPY TODAY.

39:44.616 --> 39:47.285
AND WHAT WERE YOU
BEFORE TODAY?

39:47.285 --> 39:50.556
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT WAS.

39:50.556 --> 39:52.591
THE WAY THE SUN
STRUCK THE OCEAN

39:52.591 --> 39:54.159
OR THE SOUND
OF THE WAVES.

39:54.159 --> 39:56.428
IT WAS SIMPLE,
WHATEVER IT WAS.

39:59.097 --> 40:01.667
THEN I STARTED THINKING

40:01.667 --> 40:06.037
WHEN THE LAST TIME WAS
THAT I FELT LIKE THIS.

40:06.037 --> 40:07.839
DO YOU REMEMBER?

40:13.344 --> 40:15.346
THE ONE TIME
I REMEMBER FOR SURE.

40:15.346 --> 40:17.949
I WAS WITH, UH, SAM,

40:17.949 --> 40:20.418
IN THE OCEAN,

40:20.418 --> 40:22.954
SAVING HIM
FROM THE WAVES.

40:22.954 --> 40:25.557
HE HAD HIS HEAD
ON MY SHOULDER

40:25.557 --> 40:27.526
AND WE WERE
LAUGHING.

40:30.629 --> 40:34.032
I FEEL HIS HEART
POUNDING AGAINST MY CHEST.

40:36.735 --> 40:41.339
I REMEMBER I HAD
KISSED HIS HAIR.

40:41.339 --> 40:43.575
THAT WAS BEFORE
IT WAS BLUE.

40:46.077 --> 40:48.279
YEAH.

40:48.279 --> 40:49.681
WE HAVE IT ON VIDEO.

40:49.681 --> 40:52.083
IT WAS WHEN MY PARENTS
WERE DOWN

40:52.083 --> 40:54.285
FOR HIS SIXTH BIRTHDAY.

40:54.285 --> 40:55.954
I REMEMBER THAT.

41:12.070 --> 41:13.204
I GOTTA GO.

41:13.204 --> 41:14.405
WHAT IS IT?

41:14.405 --> 41:15.507
OH,

41:15.507 --> 41:18.043
NOTHING. I'M FINE.

41:18.043 --> 41:20.946
I'LL DROP OFF YOUR LUNCH
TOMORROW.

41:27.318 --> 41:29.020
I'M GOING FOR A WALK.

41:29.020 --> 41:30.455
I NEED SOME MONEY.

41:30.455 --> 41:32.824
YOU'LL HAVE MONEY
WHEN YOU WORK.

41:35.326 --> 41:36.662
YOU'RE PREDICTABLE.

41:44.770 --> 41:47.973
YOU HAVEN'T BEEN HAPPY
IN 10 YEARS?

42:52.771 --> 42:55.807
I'M NOT DOING IT.

42:55.807 --> 42:57.676
IT'S GONNA BE GOOD.

42:57.676 --> 43:00.378
YOU KNOW,
NOBODY WOULD BLAME ME

43:00.378 --> 43:01.546
IF I LEFT.

43:01.546 --> 43:05.116
I'D BLAME YOU.
I WANT YOU HERE.

43:05.116 --> 43:08.586
WHY DON'T YOU JUST GO
AND BEG SOME MONEY OFF MY DAD

43:08.586 --> 43:11.456
SO YOU CAN MOVE
INTO SOMEPLACE DECENT,

43:11.456 --> 43:12.658
WITH A REAL KITCHEN

43:12.658 --> 43:13.992
AND A REAL BATHROOM.

43:13.992 --> 43:17.629
I'D RATHER SELL MY NUTS
TO A CASTRATI.

43:19.665 --> 43:21.332
I DON'T BEG.

43:21.332 --> 43:23.835
AND I DON'T TAKE A SHOWER
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE YARD.

43:23.835 --> 43:25.671
I CAN PROMISE YOU
COMPLETE PRIVACY.

43:25.671 --> 43:26.905
NO, YOU CAN'T!

43:26.905 --> 43:28.640
YOU CAN'T
PROMISE ME ANYTHING

43:28.640 --> 43:30.608
BECAUSE YOU DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO PROMISE.

43:30.608 --> 43:33.712
YOU LIVE IN A GARAGE, OK?

43:33.712 --> 43:35.113
YOU DON'T HAVE CABLE,

43:35.113 --> 43:36.715
YOU'RE NOT HOOKED UP
FOR THE INTERNET

43:36.715 --> 43:38.784
BECAUSE YOU DON'T EVEN OWN
A COMPUTER.

43:40.852 --> 43:43.354
AND YOU DON'T HAVE A JOB.

43:46.825 --> 43:48.626
George: JUST TRY IT.

43:48.626 --> 43:50.061
ALL I'M ASKING,

43:50.061 --> 43:51.763
JUST TRY IT.

43:54.299 --> 43:55.133
COME ON, SAM.

43:55.133 --> 43:57.468
I'M BEGGING, OK?
I'M BEGGING.

43:57.468 --> 44:00.405
GO FUCK YOURSELF.

44:13.318 --> 44:14.352
IS ALYSSA HOME?

44:14.352 --> 44:16.121
SHE WENT OUT
WITH A FRIEND.

44:16.121 --> 44:17.222
OK.

44:17.222 --> 44:19.124
SAM?

44:19.124 --> 44:20.125
UH-HUH.

44:20.125 --> 44:22.093
AH.

44:22.093 --> 44:25.563
I--I DIDN'T
RECOGNIZE YOU.

44:25.563 --> 44:27.298
UM, ALYSSA SAID
YOU TWO

44:27.298 --> 44:29.701
DON'T EVEN HAVE
PLUMBING OVER THERE.

44:29.701 --> 44:32.137
NOT A SHOWER.

44:32.137 --> 44:33.705
COME ON.

44:33.705 --> 44:35.140
COME ON.

44:41.479 --> 44:42.881
I HOPE YOUR EX-HUSBAND'S
EQUIPPED

44:42.881 --> 44:44.215
FOR THE HAVOC OF SAM,

44:44.215 --> 44:46.885
'CAUSE IT SEEMS
ABSOLUTELY BLISSFUL

44:46.885 --> 44:49.755
HERE TONIGHT.

45:03.001 --> 45:07.705
DO YOU THINK IT'S ODD
YOUR KIDS DON'T HUG YOU?

45:07.705 --> 45:08.807
SHOULD I?

45:08.807 --> 45:11.542
IT WOULD WORRY ME.

45:11.542 --> 45:14.712
IF I LET EVERYTHING THAT
SHOULD WORRY ME WORRY ME,

45:14.712 --> 45:17.682
I'D BE DEAD FROM WORRY.

45:17.682 --> 45:19.885
WHAT WOULD YOU BE

45:19.885 --> 45:21.219
IF YOU ASKED RYAN AND ADAM

45:21.219 --> 45:23.789
TO RUN IN HERE RIGHT NOW
AND HUG YOU?

45:23.789 --> 45:26.391
I'D BE YOU.

45:28.960 --> 45:32.197
I'LL DO IT
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU WANT.

45:36.868 --> 45:38.069
WHOO! WHOO!

45:38.069 --> 45:38.870
GEORGE?

45:38.870 --> 45:40.105
KURT, IS THAT YOU?

45:40.105 --> 45:43.474
THERE HAS TO BE
A LOGICAL EXPLANATION.

45:43.474 --> 45:44.609
NO HOT WATER!

45:44.609 --> 45:46.011
AH-AH-AH-AH!

45:46.011 --> 45:48.379
YOUR BUDDY, MR. DOKOS,
CALLED TO COMPLAIN

45:48.379 --> 45:50.816
THAT YOU AND A BOY
ARE SQUATTING ILLEGALLY

45:50.816 --> 45:53.351
IN YOUR GARAGE.

45:53.351 --> 45:55.253
CHECK THE PERMIT.

45:55.253 --> 45:57.655
IT WAS BUILT
AS A GUEST HOUSE.

45:57.655 --> 46:00.491
IT'S A LEGALLY
RENTABLE UNIT!

46:04.195 --> 46:06.064
NOW, THAT'S GOTTA
BE ILLEGAL.

46:09.500 --> 46:11.102
DOKOS, HUH?

46:11.102 --> 46:13.138
I'LL PISS
ON HIS LAWN.

46:13.138 --> 46:15.773
[CHUCKLES]

46:15.773 --> 46:20.812
BRO, I NEED YOU TONIGHT.

46:20.812 --> 46:24.215
I LOCKED THE DOOR.

46:24.215 --> 46:27.552
IT'LL TAKE YOU
20, 30 MINUTES.

46:27.552 --> 46:29.087
DOES ALYSSA KNOW?

46:29.087 --> 46:31.089
NO. NOTHING.
SHE SENT ME UP HERE

46:31.089 --> 46:32.690
TO SEE IF YOU WANTED
TO HANG OUT

46:32.690 --> 46:34.725
WITH HER AND HER MOM,
WATCH A MOVIE.

46:34.725 --> 46:36.294
YOU GOT ANY MORE WEED?

46:36.294 --> 46:38.729
YOU GOT ANY MONEY?

46:38.729 --> 46:41.499
300 CASH, 2 HOURS.

46:54.679 --> 46:55.981
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO DO A THING.

46:55.981 --> 46:58.016
JUST GET IN,
GET OUT.

46:58.016 --> 47:00.151
AS QUICK
AS YOU CAN.

47:01.319 --> 47:02.687
CLOSE YOUR EYES.

47:02.687 --> 47:04.289
THINK OF WHATEVER.

47:07.258 --> 47:09.961
SO, WHAT'S THE DEAL
BETWEEN YOU AND ALYSSA?

47:09.961 --> 47:11.396
DON'T EVEN.

47:11.396 --> 47:13.298
I'M THERE.

47:14.532 --> 47:16.234
I DIDN'T KNOW. SORRY.

47:16.234 --> 47:17.635
SHE WOULDN'T EVEN
FUCKIN' GO OUT WITH ME

47:17.635 --> 47:20.005
UNTIL SHE WAS 16.

47:20.005 --> 47:21.572
THAT WASN'T EVEN A RULE.

47:21.572 --> 47:24.775
THAT WAS JUST
HER OWN THING.

47:24.775 --> 47:27.312
SHE, LIKE, FIGURES
THINGS OUT ON HER OWN

47:27.312 --> 47:28.346
AND THAT'S IT.

47:28.346 --> 47:30.115
[CAR HORN HONKS]

47:37.155 --> 47:39.490
IF THIS RINGS, RUN.

47:41.192 --> 47:43.294
HE ALREADY KNOWS ABOUT
EVERYTHING YOU CAN'T DO,

47:43.294 --> 47:46.697
AND YOU CAN TELL HIM
NOT TO LOOK AT YOU

47:46.697 --> 47:48.166
IF YOU WANT.

47:49.234 --> 47:50.768
IT FEELS TOO WEIRD NOW.

47:50.768 --> 47:54.005
I DON'T--I DON'T LIKE IT.

47:58.776 --> 48:02.480
[HONK HONK]

48:02.480 --> 48:05.183
BEATS WORKIN'.

48:06.451 --> 48:08.653
YEAH.

48:11.656 --> 48:18.930
* I'M NOT SCARED *

48:20.898 --> 48:24.802
* I DON'T EVEN TRY *

48:24.802 --> 48:27.605
* I KNOW I HAVE SEEN *

48:27.605 --> 48:34.679
* THE BEST I'LL HAVE *

48:34.679 --> 48:39.884
* I DON'T EVEN TRY *

48:39.884 --> 48:47.292
* NOW THEY WANT TO TAKE
MY CHANCES *

48:48.626 --> 48:51.196
* I DON'T EVEN TRY *

48:51.196 --> 48:52.998
HEY.

48:54.099 --> 48:55.833
YOU WANT TO ROLL DOWN
THE WINDOW PLEASE?

48:55.833 --> 48:57.202
LOOK AT ME.

48:57.202 --> 48:59.437
WHAT'D YOU JUST TOSS
INTO THE BRUSH?

48:59.437 --> 49:00.471
NOTHING.

49:02.673 --> 49:04.242
HEY! HEY, YOU, KID!

49:04.242 --> 49:05.977
STOP RIGHT THERE!
HOLD IT, KID!

49:05.977 --> 49:08.546
HOLD IT!
STOP RIGHT THERE!

49:08.546 --> 49:10.315
HEY!

49:10.315 --> 49:12.483
TURN OFF
YOUR ENGINE.

49:13.718 --> 49:16.821
* LOOKS LIKE TROUBLE *

49:16.821 --> 49:20.891
* ON A RAINY DAY *

49:20.891 --> 49:23.728
* SUN STARTS SINKING *

49:23.728 --> 49:27.132
* CAN'T SEE MY SHADOW *

49:27.132 --> 49:30.568
* LOOKS LIKE TROUBLE *

49:30.568 --> 49:34.372
* ON A RAINY DAY *

49:34.372 --> 49:37.342
* HOLES UNCOVERED *

49:37.342 --> 49:40.878
* WALLS WILL CRUMBLE *

49:40.878 --> 49:43.981
* ALL SPELLS TROUBLE *

49:43.981 --> 49:51.422
* ON A RAINY DAY *

50:07.905 --> 50:09.507
GEORGE?

50:12.710 --> 50:14.112
GEORGE?

50:14.112 --> 50:16.347
GEORGE.

50:18.583 --> 50:20.451
LUNCH.

50:20.451 --> 50:23.154
LUNCH? IT'S NOT
BREAKFAST YET.

50:29.760 --> 50:33.198
OH, I DREAMED ABOUT
YOUR HOUSE LAST NIGHT.

50:33.198 --> 50:34.499
FINISHED OR UNFINISHED?

50:34.499 --> 50:36.201
NO, IT WAS PERFECT,
GEORGE.

50:36.201 --> 50:37.935
IT WAS AMAZING.

50:37.935 --> 50:39.337
HMM, AND SO REAL.

50:40.438 --> 50:42.973
DIDN'T YOU ONCE DREAM THAT
YOU COULD LICK PEOPLE WELL?

50:42.973 --> 50:46.644
THAT WASN'T A DREAM.
THAT WAS SAM.

50:46.644 --> 50:47.978
OH.

50:47.978 --> 50:50.014
RIGHT. HIS EAR INFECTION.

50:50.014 --> 50:51.616
MY TONGUE AROUND
THE EDGE OF HIS EAR

50:51.616 --> 50:53.484
IS WHAT CURED HIM.

50:53.484 --> 50:56.954
CAN YOU GO IN THAT GARAGE
AND LICK HIS ATTITUDE?

50:56.954 --> 50:59.357
THE ANTIBIOTICS
WEREN'T WORKING

50:59.357 --> 51:02.627
AND THAT IS WHAT
I BELIEVE, GEORGE.

51:06.231 --> 51:09.334
YOU WERE WRONG
ABOUT THAT FIRST YEAR.

51:16.574 --> 51:19.777
I'VE BEEN WRONG
A LOT IN MY LIFE.

51:23.614 --> 51:26.484
HINDSIGHT...

51:26.484 --> 51:28.853
IS LIKE FORESIGHT
WITHOUT A FUTURE.

51:36.594 --> 51:39.063
I HAVE 3 HOURS BEFORE
I GO GET THE KIDS.

51:39.063 --> 51:41.232
WHERE WILL I BE
MOST USEFUL?

51:41.232 --> 51:44.169
WITH YOUR HANDS
OR YOUR TONGUE?

51:44.169 --> 51:46.437
YOU'RE NOT WELL.

51:54.612 --> 51:55.546
I JUST HIT IT?

51:55.546 --> 51:56.881
HIT IT AS HARD
AS YOU CAN.

51:56.881 --> 51:58.583
THAT'S IT. YES.

52:05.256 --> 52:06.891
I SHOULD GO.

52:19.870 --> 52:20.971
George: GOOD MORNING.

52:20.971 --> 52:23.174
SAM, RYAN HAS
A GAME LATER.

52:23.174 --> 52:24.842
HE ASKED IF
YOU'D GO WATCH.

52:31.949 --> 52:34.151
GEORGE MONROE?

52:34.151 --> 52:35.152
George: ROBIN?

52:35.152 --> 52:36.687
EXCUSE ME.

52:38.256 --> 52:39.524
MR. MONROE.

52:42.026 --> 52:44.295
OH, I'VE BEEN DREADING YOU.

52:44.295 --> 52:46.664
BOB LARSON
CITY INSPECTOR.

52:46.664 --> 52:47.665
HI, BOB.

52:47.665 --> 52:50.635
YOU HAVE
AN UNENCLOSED TOILET

52:50.635 --> 52:52.270
IN PROXIMITY
TO A KITCHEN.

52:52.270 --> 52:53.271
A VIOLATION?

52:53.271 --> 52:57.041
OH, YES.

52:57.041 --> 52:58.309
UH-HUH,
AND IF I ENCLOSE IT?

52:58.309 --> 53:01.446
AN EXHAUST SYSTEM
OR A WINDOW IS CODE.

53:01.446 --> 53:03.314
HEY.

53:03.314 --> 53:04.882
WHERE IS IT?

53:04.882 --> 53:08.052
FRIEND OF YOURS IS HERE.

53:08.052 --> 53:09.687
DID YOU GO THROUGH
MY PANTS?

53:09.687 --> 53:12.357
I WANT IT BACK.
WHERE'D YOU PUT IT?

53:14.024 --> 53:15.260
I THINK I MAY HAVE
A SOLUTION.

53:15.260 --> 53:17.362
WHERE'D YOU HIDE IT, HUH?!

53:17.362 --> 53:20.164
YOU'RE UNBELIEVABLE,
YOU KNOW THAT?!

53:20.164 --> 53:21.332
WHERE IS IT?!

53:21.332 --> 53:23.634
WHAT?! DID YOU PUT IT
IN THESE SHIRTS?

53:23.634 --> 53:26.237
JUST TELL ME
WHERE IT IS!

53:26.237 --> 53:29.374
I'LL LOOK FOR IT MYSELF.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO--

53:29.374 --> 53:31.876
[CHAINSAW BUZZES]

53:42.787 --> 53:47.258
I WANT TO KNOW
WHERE IT IS NOW!

53:47.258 --> 53:49.394
YOU GOT NO RIGHT
GOING THROUGH MY THINGS,

53:49.394 --> 53:51.729
YOU KNOW THAT?
IT'S AN INVASION OF PRIVACY!

53:53.498 --> 53:55.132
I NEED THAT BACK!

53:55.132 --> 53:57.201
DOORS.

53:57.201 --> 54:00.137
I HATE TO ASK
ABOUT THE WINDOW.

54:00.137 --> 54:02.473
WHERE IS IT?!

54:02.473 --> 54:03.908
I FLUSHED IT
DOWN THE TOILET.

54:03.908 --> 54:07.878
NO!
OH, MY GOD.

54:07.878 --> 54:10.281
[CHAINSAW BUZZES]

54:21.959 --> 54:25.496
IF I HAD A GUN, I SWEAR
TO GOD I'D KILL YOU.

54:25.496 --> 54:27.432
WHAT'S IN MY PANTS

54:27.432 --> 54:29.900
IS NONE OF YOUR
FUCKING BUSINESS!

54:29.900 --> 54:31.302
LOOK, I'D SAY
YOU'RE IN COMPLIANCE.

54:31.302 --> 54:32.537
I HOPE THIS MAKES

54:32.537 --> 54:34.905
THE PAIN IN THE ASS
THAT CALLED YOU HAPPY.

54:34.905 --> 54:35.906
YOU AND ME BOTH.

54:35.906 --> 54:36.841
George: BYE!

54:36.841 --> 54:39.510
EVERYTHING ABOUT YOU
IS MY BUSINESS.

54:39.510 --> 54:41.712
WHAT YOU SMOKE,
WHAT YOU SNIFF,

54:41.712 --> 54:44.715
WHAT YOU SWALLOW--
IT'S ALL MY BUSINESS.

54:44.715 --> 54:47.518
I'VE BEEN USING
SINCE I WAS 12!

54:47.518 --> 54:51.088
YOU'RE ALSO
UNBELIEVABLY STUPID.

54:51.088 --> 54:52.557
YOU KNOW THAT?

54:52.557 --> 54:53.691
YOU DIDN'T GIVE A SHIT

54:53.691 --> 54:55.726
ABOUT ANYTHING I DID
UP UNTIL NOW.

54:55.726 --> 54:59.196
I'LL APOLOGIZE
FOR EVERYTHING BUT TODAY.

54:59.196 --> 55:01.332
TODAY I GIVE A SHIT!

55:01.332 --> 55:03.067
YEAH?
YOU'RE TOO FUCKING LATE.

55:03.067 --> 55:04.335
THESE GLOVES ARE FOR YOU.

55:04.335 --> 55:06.070
YEAH, YOU CAN'T MAKE ME
DO A THING.

55:06.070 --> 55:07.237
SIT DOWN.
NO!

55:07.237 --> 55:09.239
I'LL CALL THE COPS.
SIT!

55:09.239 --> 55:11.141
SIT DOWN!

55:11.141 --> 55:12.209
GET OFF!

55:12.209 --> 55:13.210
SIT DOWN!

55:13.210 --> 55:14.579
THAT'S CHILD ABUSE!

55:14.579 --> 55:15.913
YOU'RE IN BIG SHIT NOW.

55:15.913 --> 55:18.649
PEOPLE GO TO PRISON FOR WHAT
YOU JUST DID TO ME.

55:27.492 --> 55:30.027
MY DAD USED TO PLAY
THIS GAME.

55:30.027 --> 55:31.562
I NEVER REALLY EVEN
UNDERSTOOD WHAT IT WAS

55:31.562 --> 55:32.630
TILL AFTER HE WAS GONE.

55:32.630 --> 55:34.231
I WAS HOLDING
FOR SOMEBODY ELSE.

55:34.231 --> 55:35.633
IT WASN'T EVEN MINE.

55:35.633 --> 55:38.569
THE GAME WAS TO MAKE ME
SMALLER THAN HE WAS--

55:38.569 --> 55:41.238
SMALLER,
ALWAYS SMALLER.

55:41.238 --> 55:42.640
NO MATTER WHAT.

55:42.640 --> 55:44.475
HE COULD BE ALMOST INVISIBLE
AS A HUMAN BEING,

55:44.475 --> 55:46.877
BUT I STILL HAD TO BE
SMALLER,

55:46.877 --> 55:49.414
SO THAT IF I GOT
GOOD GRADES IN SCHOOL,

55:49.414 --> 55:51.115
THAT I WAS A PUSSY FOR
NOT PLAYING FOOTBALL,

55:51.115 --> 55:55.052
OR IF I CUT MY HAIR FOR HIM,
IT WAS NEVER SHORT ENOUGH,

55:55.052 --> 55:56.086
OR IF I SHAVED MY HEAD,

55:56.086 --> 55:57.087
THEN I LOOKED
LIKE A PSYCHO.

55:57.087 --> 55:59.790
I NEVER WON THE GAME.
NEVER.

55:59.790 --> 56:04.595
AND IF HE COULDN'T MAKE ME
SMALLER WITH WORDS...

56:10.067 --> 56:13.638
I'LL HAVE TO PAY HIM BACK.

56:17.708 --> 56:18.843
SAM...

56:21.446 --> 56:23.247
I WON'T EVER HIT YOU...

56:23.247 --> 56:25.650
EVER.

56:25.650 --> 56:27.151
I DON'T WANT YOU
SMALLER.

56:27.151 --> 56:28.218
I WANT YOU TO BE HAPPY.

56:28.218 --> 56:30.688
YOU'RE NOT.
NOT HERE WITH ME,

56:30.688 --> 56:31.722
NOT HOME
WITH YOUR MOTHER,

56:31.722 --> 56:34.058
NOT ALONE, NOT ANYWHERE.

56:34.058 --> 56:36.927
YOU'RE WHAT I WAS
MOST OF MY LIFE, SAM.

56:36.927 --> 56:38.896
I SEE IT IN YOUR EYES,
IN YOUR SLEEP,

56:38.896 --> 56:41.298
IN YOUR ANSWER
TO EVERYTHING.

56:41.298 --> 56:42.433
YOU'RE BARELY ALIVE.

56:42.433 --> 56:46.303
I'M NOT EVEN LISTENING.

56:46.303 --> 56:48.338
YOU KNOW
THE GREAT THING, THOUGH?

56:48.338 --> 56:50.475
IT'S THAT CHANGE
CAN BE SO CONSTANT

56:50.475 --> 56:52.376
THAT YOU DON'T EVEN FEEL
THE DIFFERENCE

56:52.376 --> 56:54.779
UNTIL THERE IS ONE.

56:54.779 --> 56:58.583
IT CAN BE SO SLOW
THAT YOU DON'T KNOW

56:58.583 --> 57:02.386
THAT YOUR LIFE IS BETTER
OR WORSE UNTIL IT IS.

57:02.386 --> 57:04.989
OR IT CAN JUST
BLOW YOU AWAY.

57:04.989 --> 57:07.492
MAKE YOU SOMETHING
DIFFERENT IN AN INSTANT.

57:10.961 --> 57:12.863
IT HAPPENED TO ME.

57:16.601 --> 57:18.736
BUILD THIS HOUSE
WITH ME.

57:22.206 --> 57:23.474
COME ON.

57:38.823 --> 57:40.525
FUCK.

58:53.197 --> 58:56.533
I HAVE TO PAY BACK WHAT YOU
FLUSHED DOWN THE TOILET.

58:56.533 --> 58:59.203
I WANT $10 AN HOUR,
THEN I'M DONE.

59:07.077 --> 59:09.246
THIS ALL HAS TO COME DOWN
BEFORE WE CAN START AGAIN.

59:12.983 --> 59:14.585
KNOCK IT DOWN.

59:21.826 --> 59:23.961
I HAVE HATED THIS HOUSE

59:23.961 --> 59:27.131
FROM THE MOMENT MY FATHER
PUT IT IN MY NAME.

59:27.131 --> 59:29.734
25 YEARS OF HATING
WHAT YOU LIVE IN--

59:29.734 --> 59:32.970
HATING WHAT YOU ARE!

59:32.970 --> 59:35.172
THIS IS
AN END OF IT, SAM.

59:35.172 --> 59:38.475
I'M FINALLY GONNA BUILD
SOMETHING OF MY OWN...

59:38.475 --> 59:40.878
SOMETHING I CAN BE PROUD
TO GIVE YOU.

59:40.878 --> 59:42.613
DON'T.

59:42.613 --> 59:44.949
I DON'T WANT IT.

59:44.949 --> 59:46.951
FINE. YOU CAN DO
WHATEVER YOU WANT WITH IT.

59:46.951 --> 59:48.953
ALL I WANT
IS FOR YOU TO REMEMBER

59:48.953 --> 59:50.554
THAT WE BUILT A HOUSE
TOGETHER.

59:50.554 --> 59:52.790
WE HAVEN'T BUILT SHIT.

59:52.790 --> 59:56.193
YOU'RE JUST
TEARING YOUR FATHER DOWN.

59:56.193 --> 59:58.896
TRY IT. FEELS GOOD.

01:00:12.542 --> 01:00:14.044
George: YES!

01:00:14.044 --> 01:00:15.045
GO!

01:00:28.759 --> 01:00:30.795
George: AFTER YOU.

01:00:34.331 --> 01:00:36.200
ARGH!

01:00:36.200 --> 01:00:37.267
George: THAT'S IT.

01:00:37.267 --> 01:00:38.335
YES!

01:01:00.624 --> 01:01:02.659
MORNING.

01:01:04.461 --> 01:01:05.662
YOU'RE UP EARLY.

01:02:06.223 --> 01:02:08.225
[SHOWER RUNNING]

01:02:12.129 --> 01:02:14.932
SAM, DID YOU HEAR
JOSH GOT ARRESTED?

01:02:14.932 --> 01:02:16.233
HIS PARENTS TOOK HIS CAR

01:02:16.233 --> 01:02:18.235
AND THEY'RE MAKING HIM
RIDE A BIKE ALL SUMMER.

01:02:18.235 --> 01:02:20.737
IS THIS LIKE
A PASTIME WITH PEOPLE?

01:02:20.737 --> 01:02:21.972
GO AWAY.

01:02:21.972 --> 01:02:24.975
LOOK, I'VE SEEN
LOTS OF PEOPLE.

01:02:24.975 --> 01:02:26.877
IT'S NOT A BIG THING
FOR ME.

01:02:29.513 --> 01:02:31.548
OK, COULD YOU HAND ME
A TOWEL? I'M GETTING OUT.

01:02:31.548 --> 01:02:32.850
I'M COMING IN.

01:02:32.850 --> 01:02:34.584
I DON'T WANT YOU TO.

01:02:34.584 --> 01:02:36.353
WHY ARE YOU SO UPTIGHT?

01:02:36.353 --> 01:02:38.155
I'M NOT.

01:02:38.155 --> 01:02:39.990
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS.

01:02:39.990 --> 01:02:42.759
LOOK, IT JUST MEANS
I'M GONNA SHAMPOO MY HAIR,

01:02:42.759 --> 01:02:45.329
AND, UM,
STAY OUT OF YOUR WAY.

01:02:45.329 --> 01:02:46.596
HAND ME A TOWEL.

01:02:46.596 --> 01:02:50.067
PLEASE. UM...

01:02:57.141 --> 01:02:59.476
YOU DON'T HAVE TO STAY.

01:03:23.167 --> 01:03:25.369
I THOUGHT YOU'D BE UP
WITH THE SUN.

01:03:25.369 --> 01:03:27.104
IT'S MY STUPID BACK.

01:03:27.104 --> 01:03:31.942
OH. WELL,
CAN I DO ANYTHING?

01:03:31.942 --> 01:03:33.677
RUN TO THE PHARMACY?

01:03:33.677 --> 01:03:36.746
I HAVE SOME DEMORAL
AT HOME.

01:03:36.746 --> 01:03:38.248
I, UH, TOOK SOMETHING.
I'M FINE.

01:03:49.259 --> 01:03:50.160
WHERE'S SAM?

01:03:50.160 --> 01:03:52.696
HE'S, UH--
HE WON'T USE MY SHOWER.

01:03:52.696 --> 01:03:53.998
I DON'T GET IT.

01:03:56.533 --> 01:03:58.702
YOU BROUGHT YOUR KIDS.

01:03:58.702 --> 01:03:59.937
YEAH.

01:03:59.937 --> 01:04:01.771
I KINDA SAID THAT MAYBE
THEY COULD,

01:04:01.771 --> 01:04:04.808
LIKE, DO SOMETHING.
YOU KNOW, HELP.

01:04:04.808 --> 01:04:07.011
THEY REALLY WANTED
TO COME.

01:04:07.011 --> 01:04:08.012
I REALLY WANTED TO COME.

01:04:08.012 --> 01:04:10.280
THEY WANTED
TO BE WITH ME.

01:04:10.280 --> 01:04:12.816
I DON'T THINK THEY'LL BE
TOO MUCH TROUBLE.

01:04:12.816 --> 01:04:15.619
I'LL FIND SOMETHING
THAT WON'T KILL 'EM.

01:04:15.619 --> 01:04:18.588
OR WOUND. LET THEM KEEP
THEIR EYES AND FINGERS.

01:04:20.724 --> 01:04:22.826
YOU'RE A GOOD MOTHER,
ROBIN.

01:04:22.826 --> 01:04:25.295
DO YOU NEED HELP?

01:04:25.295 --> 01:04:26.663
NO, NO.

01:04:26.663 --> 01:04:27.697
YES.

01:04:27.697 --> 01:04:29.233
COME ON.

01:04:29.233 --> 01:04:30.434
HOLD ON.

01:04:30.434 --> 01:04:31.368
OH, GOD.

01:04:31.368 --> 01:04:33.971
PUT YOUR ARM AROUND ME.
THERE WE GO.

01:04:33.971 --> 01:04:35.305
YOU DON'T WANT
TO EAT BREAKFAST?

01:04:35.305 --> 01:04:36.941
NO, THANKS.

01:04:36.941 --> 01:04:38.675
Alyssa:
GUSTER, COME HERE.

01:04:38.675 --> 01:04:41.611
SAM!

01:04:41.611 --> 01:04:43.580
WHAT WAS THAT FOR?

01:04:43.580 --> 01:04:44.714
MOM SAID I SHOULD.

01:04:44.714 --> 01:04:45.715
OH.

01:04:45.715 --> 01:04:47.717
I WOULD HAVE ANYWAY.

01:04:47.717 --> 01:04:49.053
WHO ARE YOU?

01:04:49.053 --> 01:04:50.054
WHO ARE YOU?

01:04:50.054 --> 01:04:51.055
I'M HIS BROTHER.

01:04:51.055 --> 01:04:52.722
I'M HIS FRIEND.

01:04:52.722 --> 01:04:54.491
MOM SAID WE COULD
BUILD A HOUSE.

01:04:54.491 --> 01:04:56.393
HI, ALYSSA. YOU WANT
TO BUILD A HOUSE?

01:04:56.393 --> 01:04:58.262
HI, MOM.

01:04:58.262 --> 01:05:00.730
MORNING.

01:05:00.730 --> 01:05:01.898
YOU KNOW WHAT THIS IS?

01:05:01.898 --> 01:05:03.100
THANKS FOR LETTING HIM
USE YOUR SHOWER.

01:05:03.100 --> 01:05:06.003
HE'S GOT
A STANDING INVITATION.

01:05:06.003 --> 01:05:07.804
SO YOU WANT TO BUILD
A HOUSE, HUH?

01:05:07.804 --> 01:05:09.773
THINK IT WILL STAY UP?

01:05:09.773 --> 01:05:11.541
I DON'T KNOW.

01:05:24.588 --> 01:05:25.789
ON MY SIGNAL.

01:05:25.789 --> 01:05:27.591
OK.

01:05:27.591 --> 01:05:28.625
SLOW.

01:05:28.625 --> 01:05:29.759
Alyssa: ALL RIGHT. IT'S FINE.

01:05:29.759 --> 01:05:31.161
IT'S GOOD.

01:05:31.161 --> 01:05:32.762
THROW ALL YOUR BODY WEIGHT
AGAINST IT.

01:05:32.762 --> 01:05:35.032
GOING...GOING...GOING.

01:05:35.032 --> 01:05:36.033
THERE IT IS.

01:05:36.033 --> 01:05:38.068
HA HA! OK!

01:05:38.068 --> 01:05:39.703
HOLD ON. PERFECT.

01:05:39.703 --> 01:05:44.374
Alyssa: ALL RIGHT.

01:05:44.374 --> 01:05:47.011
OVER HERE.

01:05:59.189 --> 01:06:00.957
George: GOOD, SAM.

01:06:04.061 --> 01:06:07.631
Robin: GEORGE! GEORGE!

01:06:09.333 --> 01:06:11.301
HEY, WHAT'S
GEORGE DOING?

01:06:15.105 --> 01:06:19.343
YEAH, SURE.

01:06:19.343 --> 01:06:21.945
NOT FUNNY.

01:06:21.945 --> 01:06:23.747
WHERE DO YOU
WANT THIS ONE, DAD?

01:06:23.747 --> 01:06:25.582
RIGHT UP HERE.

01:06:30.754 --> 01:06:32.489
WHOA!

01:06:34.091 --> 01:06:36.560
George: OK, HAND IT UP.

01:06:39.563 --> 01:06:42.032
Alyssa: LOOKING GOOD.
LOOKING GOOD.

01:06:42.032 --> 01:06:43.700
HI, MOM.

01:06:43.700 --> 01:06:45.669
OVER HERE.

01:06:49.106 --> 01:06:51.308
[MAN YELLING]

01:06:58.448 --> 01:06:59.616
HEY, MOM,

01:06:59.616 --> 01:07:02.686
DID YOU KNOW GEORGE
BEFORE YOU KNEW DAD?

01:07:02.686 --> 01:07:05.822
LONG BEFORE.

01:07:05.822 --> 01:07:10.060
TELL THEM HOW YOU MADE ME
FALL IN LOVE WITH YOU.

01:07:10.060 --> 01:07:13.363
I SMILED AT HIM.

01:07:13.363 --> 01:07:16.233
WATCH OUT
FOR THE SMILE, BOYS.

01:07:17.967 --> 01:07:19.636
WHO'S UP FOR A DANCE?

01:07:19.636 --> 01:07:20.637
NOT ME.

01:07:20.637 --> 01:07:22.972
OK, SAM. LET'S SEE
IF YOU REMEMBER THIS.

01:07:22.972 --> 01:07:27.077
* ROWS AND FLOWS *

01:07:27.077 --> 01:07:28.378
* OF ANGEL HAIR... *

01:07:28.378 --> 01:07:30.013
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE.

01:07:30.013 --> 01:07:33.016
* AND ICE CREAM CASTLES... *

01:07:33.016 --> 01:07:34.151
IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME.

01:07:34.151 --> 01:07:36.253
* IN THE AIR... *

01:07:36.253 --> 01:07:39.123
I USED TO ROCK YOU
TO SLEEP TO THIS.

01:07:39.123 --> 01:07:42.025
USED TO DANCE YOU TO SLEEP.

01:07:42.025 --> 01:07:44.094
COME ON. WHO'S
GONNA DANCE WITH ME?

01:07:44.094 --> 01:07:46.163
I GOT A LOT OF WORK TO DO.

01:07:46.163 --> 01:07:47.731
GEORGE?

01:07:47.731 --> 01:07:49.366
OH, NO, THANKS.

01:07:49.366 --> 01:07:50.167
ME!

01:07:50.167 --> 01:07:51.201
OH, YOU?!

01:07:51.201 --> 01:07:55.272
* FROM BOTH SIDES NOW... *

01:07:55.272 --> 01:07:59.109
OH, NOT TOO TIGHT!

01:07:59.109 --> 01:08:02.279
* STILL SOMEHOW *

01:08:02.279 --> 01:08:07.484
* IT'S CLOUD ILLUSIONS
I RECALL... *

01:08:07.484 --> 01:08:08.818
OK, THAT'S ENOUGH
FOR TODAY.

01:08:08.818 --> 01:08:09.953
I GOT A LOT OF WORK
TO DO.

01:08:09.953 --> 01:08:11.921
* I REALLY
DON'T KNOW CLOUDS *

01:08:11.921 --> 01:08:12.989
COME ON, GEORGE.

01:08:12.989 --> 01:08:14.023
SEE IF YOU'VE GOTTEN
ANY BETTER.

01:08:14.023 --> 01:08:16.725
OH, NO, NO, NO.
WORSE. WORSE.

01:08:16.725 --> 01:08:19.263
* AT ALL *

01:08:23.433 --> 01:08:29.538
* TEARS AND FEARS
AND FEELING PROUD *

01:08:29.538 --> 01:08:36.313
* TO SAY "I LOVE YOU"
RIGHT OUT LOUD *

01:08:36.313 --> 01:08:40.015
* WELL, SOMETHING'S LOST *

01:08:40.015 --> 01:08:42.986
* BUT SOMETHING'S GAINED *

01:08:42.986 --> 01:08:45.389
* IN LIVING EVERY DAY *

01:08:45.389 --> 01:08:47.122
I THINK I'M GONNA GO HOME.

01:08:47.122 --> 01:08:49.225
SEE YOU TOMORROW.

01:08:49.225 --> 01:08:50.327
* I'VE LOOKED AT LIFE *

01:08:50.327 --> 01:08:54.464
* FROM BOTH SIDES NOW *

01:08:54.464 --> 01:08:56.800
* FROM WIN AND LOSE *

01:08:56.800 --> 01:09:00.770
* AND STILL SOMEHOW *

01:09:00.770 --> 01:09:06.609
* IT'S LIFE'S ILLUSIONS
I RECALL *

01:09:06.609 --> 01:09:14.082
* I REALLY DON'T KNOW LIFE *

01:09:14.082 --> 01:09:19.423
* AT ALL *

01:09:49.486 --> 01:09:52.721
I TOOK SOME OF YOUR VICODIN.

01:09:52.721 --> 01:09:54.691
I KNOW.

01:09:58.728 --> 01:10:00.730
WHY?

01:10:02.198 --> 01:10:05.469
I LIKE HOW IT FEELS
NOT TO FEEL.

01:10:05.469 --> 01:10:07.904
I KNOW THE FEELING.

01:10:16.446 --> 01:10:19.549
HOW DO YOU BECOME SOMETHING
THAT YOU'RE NOT?

01:10:19.549 --> 01:10:22.752
WHAT WOULD YOU
LIKE TO BE?

01:10:22.752 --> 01:10:24.821
WHAT I'M NOT.

01:10:24.821 --> 01:10:26.756
WHAT ARE YOU NOW?

01:10:26.756 --> 01:10:29.726
I'M NOTHING.

01:10:29.726 --> 01:10:31.561
IT'S NOT TRUE.

01:10:31.561 --> 01:10:34.130
YOU SEE,
THAT'S THE THING, THOUGH,

01:10:34.130 --> 01:10:37.233
IS THAT
I AM WHAT I SAY I AM.

01:10:37.233 --> 01:10:40.437
I GAVE UP ON YOU.

01:10:40.437 --> 01:10:43.106
NO, NO.
IF YOU'D GIVEN UP ON ME,

01:10:43.106 --> 01:10:44.508
I'D BE IN TAHOE RIGHT NOW.

01:10:44.508 --> 01:10:47.777
WHAT WOULD YOU BE DOING
THERE RIGHT NOW?

01:10:49.946 --> 01:10:52.316
GETTING HIGH, I GUESS.

01:10:52.316 --> 01:10:55.819
IF I ASKED YOU TO STOP,
WOULD YOU?

01:10:57.487 --> 01:11:01.057
I HAVEN'T USED ANYTHING
IN 2 DAYS.

01:11:01.057 --> 01:11:03.527
I'M TRYING.

01:11:03.527 --> 01:11:06.296
I'M PROUD OF YOU.

01:11:08.498 --> 01:11:09.866
YEAH, WELL, DON'T BE.

01:11:12.201 --> 01:11:13.870
AND HIDE THOSE...

01:11:13.870 --> 01:11:19.208
THEY--WHATEVER THAT
NEW DRUG IS YOU HAVE.

01:11:19.208 --> 01:11:21.545
I LIKE IT.

01:11:32.155 --> 01:11:35.158
I PUT A GUN TO
MY FATHER'S HEAD ONCE.

01:11:35.158 --> 01:11:37.126
YOU EVER THINK
LIKE THAT?

01:11:37.126 --> 01:11:38.895
HE WAS PASSED OUT.

01:11:38.895 --> 01:11:42.366
JUST BEEN YELLING AT
MY MOM OVER NOTHING...

01:11:42.366 --> 01:11:44.968
UNDER-COOKED MEAT.

01:11:44.968 --> 01:11:46.503
I WENT TO MY ROOM.

01:11:46.503 --> 01:11:48.738
I HELD THE BARREL
RIGHT UP TO HIS EAR...

01:11:50.640 --> 01:11:53.410
AND THEN I CHICKENED OUT
AGAIN.

01:12:00.684 --> 01:12:01.918
'COURSE,
IT WAS A BB GUN,

01:12:01.918 --> 01:12:03.553
BUT STILL, IT WOULD
HAVE HURT LIKE HELL.

01:12:05.288 --> 01:12:07.190
ARE YOU TALKING?

01:12:07.190 --> 01:12:10.193
I WAS JUST THINKING
ABOUT MY MOM.

01:12:10.193 --> 01:12:11.961
SHE WOULDN'T LEAVE
MY DAD.

01:12:11.961 --> 01:12:14.464
I REMEMBER ONCE
SHE MADE DINNER FOR US

01:12:14.464 --> 01:12:17.133
WEARING SUNGLASSES.

01:12:17.133 --> 01:12:19.168
MIND YOU,
IT WAS DARK OUTSIDE...

01:12:19.168 --> 01:12:21.671
AND IN.

01:12:21.671 --> 01:12:25.709
AND NOBODY SAID A THING
ABOUT IT.

01:12:28.344 --> 01:12:31.047
WHY WOULDN'T SHE
JUST LEAVE?

01:12:31.047 --> 01:12:35.018
I THINK SHE WAS TERRIFIED
TO LIVE WITH HIM, BUT, UM...

01:12:35.018 --> 01:12:38.121
MAYBE EVEN MORE TERRIFIED
OF LIFE WITHOUT HIM.

01:12:38.121 --> 01:12:41.057
I WOULD HAVE KILLED HIM.

01:12:41.057 --> 01:12:44.428
WOULD HAVE BEEN SO
MUCH BETTER IF YOU HAD.

01:12:44.428 --> 01:12:48.398
THEN MAYBE HE WOULDN'T
HAVE DRIVEN DRUNK...

01:12:51.234 --> 01:12:52.636
MAYBE HE WOULDN'T HAVE
KILLED MY MOM

01:12:52.636 --> 01:12:53.903
IN THE CAR CRASH...

01:12:53.903 --> 01:12:57.841
THE WOMAN
IN THE OTHER CAR...

01:12:57.841 --> 01:13:00.910
HURT A LITTLE GIRL
IN THE BACKSEAT, TOO.

01:13:03.680 --> 01:13:05.314
YOU WOULD HAVE LIKED
YOUR GRANDMOTHER.

01:13:05.314 --> 01:13:07.851
SHE WAS PRETTY COOL.

01:13:07.851 --> 01:13:10.720
I STILL THINK
ABOUT THAT LITTLE GIRL.

01:13:10.720 --> 01:13:13.022
THEY COULDN'T FIND
HER FATHER,

01:13:13.022 --> 01:13:14.624
AND HER MOTHER WAS DEAD.

01:13:18.294 --> 01:13:21.164
YOU EVER WISH
YOU'D DONE IT?

01:13:21.164 --> 01:13:23.633
WHAT? KILLED MY DAD?

01:13:26.369 --> 01:13:28.605
I LOVED HIM TOO MUCH.

01:13:32.108 --> 01:13:33.810
THAT'S WEIRD.

01:13:40.116 --> 01:13:41.851
YEAH, I GUESS IT IS.

01:14:06.776 --> 01:14:08.411
YOU KNOW
WHAT I'VE DECIDED?

01:14:08.411 --> 01:14:11.981
WE SHOULD
TAKE A VACATION...

01:14:11.981 --> 01:14:13.950
JUST THE TWO OF US.

01:14:18.087 --> 01:14:21.591
I'D LOVE TO DRIVE
THROUGH NEW ENGLAND IN THE FALL.

01:14:21.591 --> 01:14:23.159
SOONER THAN THE FALL.

01:14:30.534 --> 01:14:33.870
I'M HELPING GEORGE
WITH HIS HOUSE.

01:14:33.870 --> 01:14:36.205
WHAT?

01:14:36.205 --> 01:14:39.008
I'VE BEEN HELPING HIM
THE LAST FEW DAYS--

01:14:39.008 --> 01:14:41.010
WEEKS, ACTUALLY.

01:14:41.010 --> 01:14:41.945
SAM'S WORKING.

01:14:41.945 --> 01:14:45.181
WELL, GOOD.
THAT'S GREAT.

01:14:45.181 --> 01:14:46.883
THAT WAS THE PLAN.

01:14:48.184 --> 01:14:51.655
WE COULDN'T STAND HIM,
AND GEORGE NEEDED HELP.

01:14:51.655 --> 01:14:53.690
I CAN'T GO RIGHT NOW.

01:14:56.425 --> 01:14:58.528
YOU CAN'T GO
BECAUSE OF SAM?

01:15:00.597 --> 01:15:04.033
WE HAVEN'T BEEN AWAY
TOGETHER FOR 3--

01:15:04.033 --> 01:15:06.703
3 YEARS.

01:15:06.703 --> 01:15:09.505
WHAT DIFFERENCE IS
A FEW MONTHS GONNA MAKE?

01:15:09.505 --> 01:15:11.675
YOU CAN'T GO WITH ME
BECAUSE OF SAM.

01:15:11.675 --> 01:15:13.977
SAM'S WORKING AT SOMETHING

01:15:13.977 --> 01:15:16.813
FOR THE FIRST TIME
IN HIS ENTIRE LIFE.

01:15:16.813 --> 01:15:19.315
ONCE IN A WHILE
HE EVEN TALKS TO ME.

01:15:19.315 --> 01:15:20.617
I WANT TO BE AROUND FOR THAT.

01:15:20.617 --> 01:15:22.919
SO AM I, ROBIN. I'M WORKING
AT SOMETHING, TOO.

01:15:22.919 --> 01:15:25.789
I'M EVEN TALKING. YOU WANT
TO BE AROUND FOR THAT?

01:15:27.591 --> 01:15:29.292
I DON'T KNOW.

01:15:37.033 --> 01:15:39.035
[GUSTER BARKING]

01:15:43.206 --> 01:15:44.741
HEY! THAT IS MINE!

01:15:44.741 --> 01:15:47.276
PUT THAT DOWN RIGHT NOW!
PUT THAT DOWN RIGHT NOW.

01:15:47.276 --> 01:15:48.912
[GROWLING]

01:15:48.912 --> 01:15:50.580
YOU ARE IN BIG TROUBLE,
MISTER!

01:15:50.580 --> 01:15:51.948
YOU DON'T EVEN UNDERSTAND.

01:15:51.948 --> 01:15:54.417
GEORGE! I'M GOING TO KILL YOU
FOR THIS!

01:15:54.417 --> 01:15:55.985
I PROMISE YOU.
I'M GOING TO SUE YOU!

01:15:55.985 --> 01:15:57.887
I'M SUING YOUR DOG!
GEORGE!

01:15:57.887 --> 01:16:01.157
YOU SON OF A BITCH!
THIS IS YOUR FAULT!

01:16:01.157 --> 01:16:04.093
THESE CLOTHES ARE WORTH
A FORTUNE--A FORTUNE!

01:16:08.297 --> 01:16:10.066
WHAT'S THE POINT OF THIS?

01:16:10.066 --> 01:16:12.702
DOES EVERYTHING
HAVE TO HAVE A POINT?

01:16:12.702 --> 01:16:15.805
ARE YOU SURE THAT YOU'RE
TOTALLY INTO GUYS?

01:16:15.805 --> 01:16:18.908
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

01:16:18.908 --> 01:16:21.210
JUST--JOSH KINDA SAID--

01:16:21.210 --> 01:16:24.313
I'M NOT GAY.

01:16:24.313 --> 01:16:27.717
I MEAN, HELLO!

01:16:29.452 --> 01:16:30.987
YEAH, I WAS--I WAS WONDERING.

01:16:32.789 --> 01:16:34.891
YOU'RE DRIVING ME CRAZY,
YOU KNOW THAT?

01:16:34.891 --> 01:16:37.761
YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE

01:16:37.761 --> 01:16:40.396
TRYING TO JACK OFF
IN AN ARMOIRE?

01:16:40.396 --> 01:16:41.665
NO, NOT REALLY.

01:16:41.665 --> 01:16:44.333
NO, YOU'RE OFF,
YOU KNOW? YOU'RE...

01:16:46.670 --> 01:16:48.071
YOU'RE WAY OFF.

01:16:48.071 --> 01:16:51.007
LOOK, I THOUGHT
I WAS HELPING YOU.

01:16:53.209 --> 01:16:55.111
IT WOULD HELP ME
IF I COULD KISS YOU.

01:16:55.111 --> 01:16:57.080
NO.

01:16:57.080 --> 01:16:59.883
LOOK, I THOUGHT
WE WERE JUST FRIENDS.

01:17:01.084 --> 01:17:03.219
WELL...WHAT YOU THINK
YOU KNOW

01:17:03.219 --> 01:17:07.290
DOESN'T NECESSARILY
HAVE MUCH TO DO WITH REALITY.

01:17:07.290 --> 01:17:11.327
I MEAN, I HOPE I'M NOT
THE FIRST TO SAY THIS ABOUT YOU.

01:17:11.327 --> 01:17:12.996
ALL RIGHT.

01:17:12.996 --> 01:17:15.431
BUT THEN WE'RE JUST
GONNA BE FRIENDS, OK?

01:17:15.431 --> 01:17:17.200
YEAH, OK.

01:17:38.154 --> 01:17:39.756
AHHH!

01:17:39.756 --> 01:17:41.290
OH, YUCK!

01:17:41.290 --> 01:17:44.660
OH, YOU'RE SCRUBBING DOWN
THE SHOWER.

01:17:58.274 --> 01:18:00.877
Alyssa: YOU MUST HAVE
A REALLY GREAT HUSBAND.

01:18:00.877 --> 01:18:02.645
Robin: WHY IS THAT?

01:18:02.645 --> 01:18:04.580
WELL, NO, IT'S JUST--

01:18:04.580 --> 01:18:06.149
I MEAN, YOU'RE HERE
EVERY SINGLE DAY.

01:18:06.149 --> 01:18:08.684
HE'S AT WORK
WHILE I'M HERE.

01:18:10.153 --> 01:18:13.222
I GUESS I WOULD JUST BE
JEALOUS, IF I WERE HIM.

01:18:13.222 --> 01:18:15.959
HE HAS NOTHING
TO WORRY ABOUT.

01:18:15.959 --> 01:18:18.127
HE'S NOT THE TYPE TO WORRY.

01:18:18.127 --> 01:18:18.928
HERE YOU GO.

01:18:18.928 --> 01:18:20.596
ALL RIGHT, LET'S EAT.

01:18:20.596 --> 01:18:22.531
GEORGE?

01:18:22.531 --> 01:18:25.769
GEORGE!

01:18:25.769 --> 01:18:28.104
LUNCH.

01:18:29.505 --> 01:18:32.441
OHH.

01:18:32.441 --> 01:18:34.377
WHO WANTS CHEESE?

01:18:34.377 --> 01:18:37.180
ME!

01:18:37.180 --> 01:18:39.348
THANK YOU.

01:18:43.652 --> 01:18:44.653
[SEAGULL CAWS]

01:18:44.653 --> 01:18:46.923
WHAT?

01:18:53.096 --> 01:18:54.097
NOTHING.

01:18:57.901 --> 01:19:01.070
NOTHING "R," OK?

01:19:01.070 --> 01:19:04.073
ENOUGH FOR DRINKS,
POPCORN, AND CANDY.

01:19:04.073 --> 01:19:06.342
AND VIDEO GAMES AFTER!

01:19:06.342 --> 01:19:07.777
HOME AFTER.

01:19:07.777 --> 01:19:09.345
WILL YOU COME IN
AND SAY HI?

01:19:09.345 --> 01:19:11.114
MAYBE.

01:19:11.114 --> 01:19:13.349
SEATBELT.

01:19:13.349 --> 01:19:14.617
SHE HAVE TO COME?

01:19:14.617 --> 01:19:16.385
DEFINITELY.
HERE, BUCKLE UP.

01:19:21.190 --> 01:19:23.392
I SHOULD GO.

01:19:23.392 --> 01:19:25.394
[BREATHLESS]

01:19:26.529 --> 01:19:27.530
[GUSTER BARKS]

01:19:27.530 --> 01:19:28.564
IT WOULD BE BETTER

01:19:28.564 --> 01:19:29.565
IF YOU DIDN'T
COME EVERY DAY.

01:19:29.565 --> 01:19:33.636
WHY? I LIKE
BEING WITH SAM.

01:19:33.636 --> 01:19:34.838
BUT THERE'S
LESS AND LESS

01:19:34.838 --> 01:19:37.006
FOR RYAN AND ADAM
TO DO AND...

01:19:37.006 --> 01:19:38.007
I'D HATE
FOR THE BOYS

01:19:38.007 --> 01:19:39.275
TO BE BORED,
YOU KNOW.

01:19:39.275 --> 01:19:41.610
WELL, I KNOW THEY DON'T
HELP MUCH ANY MORE,

01:19:41.610 --> 01:19:43.646
BUT THEY LOVE
COMING HERE, GEORGE.

01:19:43.646 --> 01:19:45.514
BUT, UH...

01:19:48.684 --> 01:19:49.685
HOW MUCH TIME
DO THEY GET

01:19:49.685 --> 01:19:50.686
TO SPEND
WITH THEIR DAD?

01:19:50.686 --> 01:19:53.622
WHAT IS THIS?

01:19:53.622 --> 01:19:56.492
YOU KNOW, ALYSSA THINKS
SOMETHING'S UP WITH US.

01:19:56.492 --> 01:19:58.794
SHE KEEPS GIVING ME CRAP
ABOUT BEING AWAY FROM PETER,

01:19:58.794 --> 01:20:00.663
AND NOW
YOU'RE DOING IT, TOO.

01:20:00.663 --> 01:20:04.600
NO ONE REALIZES
THAT HE'S NOT THERE.

01:20:04.600 --> 01:20:06.302
HE'S NEVER THERE.

01:20:06.302 --> 01:20:09.038
EVEN WHEN HE IS,
HE ISN'T...

01:20:09.038 --> 01:20:10.974
SO IF YOU DON'T
WANT ME HERE

01:20:10.974 --> 01:20:13.943
OR YOU DON'T WANT
MY CHILDREN HERE, THEN...

01:20:13.943 --> 01:20:18.281
SAY IT.
I'LL STOP COMING...

01:20:18.281 --> 01:20:19.682
BUT IT WON'T BE
BECAUSE OF PETER.

01:20:19.682 --> 01:20:22.185
IT'LL BE BECAUSE
YOU TOLD ME TO.

01:20:22.185 --> 01:20:24.253
SO SAY WHAT
YOU HAVE TO SAY,

01:20:24.253 --> 01:20:26.289
BECAUSE I'M NOT LEAVING
TILL I HEAR IT.

01:20:28.191 --> 01:20:31.160
I'D RATHER
YOU NOT BE HERE.

01:20:36.265 --> 01:20:37.566
I THOUGHT
WE WERE HELPING.

01:20:40.236 --> 01:20:41.470
[CAR BEEPS]

01:21:03.359 --> 01:21:04.360
[KNOCKS]

01:21:06.595 --> 01:21:07.596
HI.
HEY.

01:21:07.596 --> 01:21:09.132
IS ALYSSA HOME?

01:21:09.132 --> 01:21:11.834
OH, NO. SHE WENT OUT
WITH SOME FRIENDS.

01:21:11.834 --> 01:21:13.869
WHAT FRIENDS
DID SHE GO WITH?

01:21:13.869 --> 01:21:15.138
I DON'T KNOW.

01:21:15.138 --> 01:21:16.439
YOU CAN COME IN
AND WAIT

01:21:16.439 --> 01:21:17.506
IF YOU LIKE.

01:21:17.506 --> 01:21:19.675
OK, THANKS, MRS. BECK.

01:21:19.675 --> 01:21:20.676
Coleen:
CAN I GET YOU

01:21:20.676 --> 01:21:21.677
SOMETHING
TO DRINK, JOSH?

01:21:21.677 --> 01:21:22.745
Josh: NO, THANKS.

01:21:22.745 --> 01:21:23.947
ALYSSA MAY BE
A WHILE, YOU KNOW.

01:21:23.947 --> 01:21:25.881
YOU SURE YOU DON'T
WANT ANYTHING?

01:21:28.017 --> 01:21:30.486
GOT A BEER?

01:21:30.486 --> 01:21:32.221
A BEER?

01:21:33.889 --> 01:21:35.558
A BEER.

01:21:44.367 --> 01:21:45.301
WHAT HAPPENED?

01:21:45.301 --> 01:21:48.371
NOTHING IS GOING ON
WITH US, IS IT?

01:21:50.373 --> 01:21:51.440
GOING ON?

01:21:51.440 --> 01:21:52.942
WHEN I PICKED YOU
UP FROM THE TRAIN,

01:21:52.942 --> 01:21:55.744
WHAT YOU SAID,
WHAT--WHAT WAS THAT?

01:21:55.744 --> 01:21:57.380
WHAT DID I SAY?

01:21:57.380 --> 01:21:58.781
OH, YOU KNOW.

01:21:58.781 --> 01:22:00.216
WHAT?
YOU...

01:22:00.216 --> 01:22:01.850
THE THING ABOUT
ME BEING THE--

01:22:01.850 --> 01:22:03.152
THE MOST
BEAUTIFUL PERSON.

01:22:03.152 --> 01:22:04.520
WHAT WAS THAT, HMM?

01:22:04.520 --> 01:22:06.055
THAT WAS THE TRUTH.

01:22:06.055 --> 01:22:07.656
YOU'VE NEVER
SAID THAT BEFORE.

01:22:10.159 --> 01:22:11.560
I--I MIGHT SAY
A LOT OF THINGS

01:22:11.560 --> 01:22:12.895
I'VE NEVER SAID BEFORE.

01:22:12.895 --> 01:22:14.563
IT SOUNDED LIKE
A PICKUP LINE.

01:22:16.899 --> 01:22:18.101
I CAN'T PICK YOU UP?

01:22:18.101 --> 01:22:20.003
I'M MARRIED.

01:22:20.003 --> 01:22:22.171
YOU GET MY THINKING.

01:22:22.171 --> 01:22:23.706
IF I WEREN'T MARRIED?

01:22:23.706 --> 01:22:26.709
SHOULD WE DO THIS?

01:22:26.709 --> 01:22:29.945
I NEED TO KNOW.

01:22:29.945 --> 01:22:33.949
WHAT? DO I STILL
LOVE YOU?

01:22:35.951 --> 01:22:37.153
ABSOLUTELY.

01:22:44.860 --> 01:22:47.096
[SIGHS]

01:22:47.096 --> 01:22:49.865
THERE'S NOT
A DOUBT IN MY MIND.

01:22:49.865 --> 01:22:53.102
THROUGH ALL
MY ANGER, MY EGO,

01:22:53.102 --> 01:22:54.237
I WAS ALWAYS
FAITHFUL

01:22:54.237 --> 01:22:56.705
IN MY LOVE FOR YOU.

01:22:56.705 --> 01:22:58.441
THAT I MADE YOU
DOUBT IT...

01:23:01.077 --> 01:23:02.211
THAT IS
THE GREAT MISTAKE

01:23:02.211 --> 01:23:04.147
OF A LIFE
FULL OF MISTAKES.

01:23:06.515 --> 01:23:08.717
THE TRUTH DOESN'T
SET US FREE, ROBIN.

01:23:08.717 --> 01:23:10.019
I CAN TELL YOU
I LOVE YOU

01:23:10.019 --> 01:23:11.687
AS MANY
TIMES AS YOU

01:23:11.687 --> 01:23:12.688
CAN STAND
TO HEAR IT,

01:23:12.688 --> 01:23:13.522
AND ALL THAT DOES,

01:23:13.522 --> 01:23:16.559
THE ONLY THING
IS REMIND US...

01:23:16.559 --> 01:23:21.764
LOVE IS NOT ENOUGH.
NOT EVEN CLOSE.

01:23:31.274 --> 01:23:33.576
I--I--I'VE GOTTA...

01:23:56.832 --> 01:23:58.201
OH, GOD.

01:24:00.336 --> 01:24:01.804
HEY. OH, NO,
NO, NO, NO.

01:24:01.804 --> 01:24:03.239
THESE AREN'T FOR YOU.

01:24:09.078 --> 01:24:10.713
NO.

01:24:13.048 --> 01:24:15.484
NO. NO.

01:24:24.893 --> 01:24:27.363
Peter: ALL I AM
IS WHAT I HAVE.

01:24:27.363 --> 01:24:30.499
GOD, THAT SOUNDS
PATHETIC, DOESN'T IT?

01:24:35.371 --> 01:24:37.106
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HOME?

01:24:37.106 --> 01:24:40.776
I ALWAYS FELT THAT
I COULD NEVER MARRY YOU

01:24:40.776 --> 01:24:41.910
WITHOUT FIRST SHOWING YOU

01:24:41.910 --> 01:24:44.647
WHAT A FABULOUS LIFE
YOU COULD LIVE, DESPITE ME.

01:24:44.647 --> 01:24:45.914
[LAUGHS]

01:24:45.914 --> 01:24:48.016
YOU NEVER REALLY
TRUSTED ME.

01:24:48.016 --> 01:24:49.252
YOU HAVE A FABULOUS
LIFE, ROBIN.

01:24:49.252 --> 01:24:52.288
DESPITE YOU.

01:24:54.723 --> 01:24:55.924
WHERE ARE THE KIDS?

01:24:55.924 --> 01:24:58.127
SAM TOOK THEM
TO A MOVIE.

01:25:03.065 --> 01:25:05.601
WELL, I'LL BE, UH...

01:25:05.601 --> 01:25:07.303
IN THE BEDROOM.

01:25:46.309 --> 01:25:48.377
I FELL ASLEEP.

01:25:51.547 --> 01:25:55.751
I NEED TO ASK YOU
SOMETHING, MR. MONROE.

01:25:55.751 --> 01:25:58.721
DO--DO YOU NEED
TO ASK ME LIKE THAT?

01:25:58.721 --> 01:26:03.192
I WANT YOU TO TRY
SOMETHING WITH ME.

01:26:03.192 --> 01:26:07.463
I'M ON A LOT
OF MORPHINE RIGHT NOW--

01:26:07.463 --> 01:26:09.832
ORAL MORPHINE
FOR MY BACK.

01:26:09.832 --> 01:26:13.536
CAN I WAIT TILL I CAN
SAY NO AND SOUND CONVINCING?

01:26:32.821 --> 01:26:34.156
DID YOU FEEL ANYTHING?

01:26:34.156 --> 01:26:36.325
UH...

01:26:37.826 --> 01:26:40.629
MAYBE A TONGUE.

01:26:40.629 --> 01:26:43.532
MY MOUTH IS NUMB.
I'M NOT SURE.

01:26:43.532 --> 01:26:46.335
[SIGHS]

01:26:46.335 --> 01:26:48.404
WHY DID YOU DO THAT?

01:26:48.404 --> 01:26:50.373
WHEN YOU WERE
DATING MY MOM,

01:26:50.373 --> 01:26:54.743
I SAW YOU KISS
HER ONCE, AND...

01:26:54.743 --> 01:26:56.745
YOU LOOK LIKE
SUCH A GOOD KISSER.

01:27:00.416 --> 01:27:04.186
MY MOM WOULD DIE.
[LAUGHS]

01:27:04.186 --> 01:27:05.854
George: LET'S SHUT UP
AND LET HER LIVE.

01:27:05.854 --> 01:27:08.724
OH, MRS. BECK!
MY GOD.

01:27:12.495 --> 01:27:15.898
Alyssa: IT'S NOT WHAT
I WAS EXPECTING.

01:27:15.898 --> 01:27:17.866
George: WHAT DID YOU
THINK IT WOULD BE?

01:27:17.866 --> 01:27:20.002
I DON'T KNOW...

01:27:20.002 --> 01:27:24.273
MORE LIKE
WHEN I KISS SAM.

01:27:24.273 --> 01:27:25.674
YEAH,
MORE LIKE THAT.

01:27:25.674 --> 01:27:27.142
OH.

01:27:27.142 --> 01:27:28.744
THANKS FOR YOUR
TIME, THOUGH.

01:27:28.744 --> 01:27:30.446
HEY, PFFT.

01:27:35.250 --> 01:27:36.452
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:27:38.421 --> 01:27:42.224
[LAUGHS]
AH.

01:27:42.224 --> 01:27:44.793
[ALARM BLARES]
Alyssa: MOM?

01:27:44.793 --> 01:27:46.495
[GASPS]

01:27:46.495 --> 01:27:48.263
OH, GOD. OH, GOD.

01:27:48.263 --> 01:27:49.264
GET DRESSED.

01:27:49.264 --> 01:27:50.265
Alyssa: MOM?
GET DRESSED.

01:27:50.265 --> 01:27:51.266
WHERE ARE MY CLOTHES?
NOW!

01:27:51.266 --> 01:27:52.267
DO YOU KNOW
THE ALARM IS ON?

01:27:52.267 --> 01:27:54.269
[BEEPS, STOPS]

01:27:54.269 --> 01:27:56.972
Alyssa: MOM!

01:27:56.972 --> 01:27:58.173
WHERE ARE YOU?

01:27:58.173 --> 01:28:00.609
[GRUNTS]

01:28:00.609 --> 01:28:02.277
MOM!

01:28:02.277 --> 01:28:04.313
MOM?

01:28:04.313 --> 01:28:06.048
Coleen: UH,
IN HERE, HONEY.

01:28:06.048 --> 01:28:08.851
HI. HI.

01:28:08.851 --> 01:28:10.886
JOSH.

01:28:12.388 --> 01:28:13.922
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS DOING?

01:28:13.922 --> 01:28:15.924
I PUT HIM TO WORK.

01:28:17.460 --> 01:28:20.329
GOOD. OH, GOOD.
IT'S FIXED.

01:28:20.329 --> 01:28:22.598
[TOILET FLUSHES]

01:28:22.598 --> 01:28:25.634
Adam and Ryan: NO, NO, NO!
I'M GOIN', I'M GOIN', I'M GOIN'!

01:28:28.471 --> 01:28:30.072
I GOT TO PLAY
ONE VIDEO GAME

01:28:30.072 --> 01:28:32.107
FOR 3 HOURS
STRAIGHT!

01:28:32.107 --> 01:28:33.308
THERE WERE NO PGs,

01:28:33.308 --> 01:28:34.910
SO I JUST GAVE 'EM MONEY
FOR VIDEO GAMES.

01:28:36.144 --> 01:28:37.946
GO TELL YOUR DAD
DINNER'S READY.

01:28:37.946 --> 01:28:40.349
HE'S IN THE BEDROOM.

01:28:40.349 --> 01:28:43.852
ARE YOU STAYING
FOR DINNER?

01:28:43.852 --> 01:28:45.821
IT DEPENDS ON WHAT
I'D GIVE UP ON.

01:28:45.821 --> 01:28:48.056
LASAGNA.

01:28:48.056 --> 01:28:50.559
OH, SEE THAT?
THAT'S A TRAP.

01:28:52.461 --> 01:28:53.829
HE'S NOT THERE.

01:28:53.829 --> 01:28:56.532
YEAH.

01:28:56.532 --> 01:28:57.833
NO, HE'S NOT.

01:28:59.968 --> 01:29:01.136
PETER?

01:29:01.136 --> 01:29:02.871
Man: HEY, WAIT!

01:29:02.871 --> 01:29:05.774
[BARKS]
GET!

01:29:05.774 --> 01:29:06.909
GOD, I'M GONNA
GET YOU!

01:29:06.909 --> 01:29:08.243
Woman: THE MAN WHO
HAS NEVER CHANGED

01:29:08.243 --> 01:29:10.379
FROM THE DAY WE MOVED IN.

01:29:10.379 --> 01:29:13.148
MIND YOUR OWN
FUCKING BUSINESS.

01:29:13.148 --> 01:29:14.983
TOM, GET IN THE CAR.

01:29:17.553 --> 01:29:18.754
YOU BELIEVE THAT?

01:29:34.470 --> 01:29:35.671
[SIGHS]

01:29:48.250 --> 01:29:50.586
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

01:29:52.154 --> 01:29:53.388
[RING]

01:29:53.388 --> 01:29:54.389
HELLO?

01:29:54.389 --> 01:29:55.591
Josh: I DON'T SEE ALYSSA.

01:29:55.591 --> 01:29:58.126
JUST PLEASE OPEN THE DOOR
WHEN I KNOCK.

01:29:58.126 --> 01:30:00.463
JUST COME ON UP.

01:30:10.473 --> 01:30:12.340
JOSH.

01:30:12.340 --> 01:30:13.842
ALYSSA.

01:30:13.842 --> 01:30:15.310
Alyssa:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:30:15.310 --> 01:30:17.946
Josh: I WAS WONDERING,
YOU KNOW...

01:30:17.946 --> 01:30:21.817
IF YOU'D LIKE
TO GO FOR A RIDE?

01:30:21.817 --> 01:30:23.952
WELL, DO YOU WANNA
HELP US OUT?

01:30:23.952 --> 01:30:27.289
GEORGE IS PAYING SAM,
LIKE, $10 AN HOUR.

01:30:27.289 --> 01:30:30.726
300 CASH, 2 HOURS.
THAT'S IT.

01:30:30.726 --> 01:30:32.027
WHAT?

01:30:32.027 --> 01:30:33.596
JUST A JOKE.

01:30:33.596 --> 01:30:35.363
JUST A STUPID JOKE.

01:30:35.363 --> 01:30:37.766
VERY FUNNY.

01:30:45.107 --> 01:30:49.444
Robin: OH, IS YOUR BACK
STILL KILLING YOU?

01:30:49.444 --> 01:30:52.581
UH, YEAH.

01:30:52.581 --> 01:30:55.183
I DIDN'T, UH...

01:30:55.183 --> 01:30:57.052
I DIDN'T
EXPECT YOU TODAY.

01:30:58.821 --> 01:31:01.657
I KEPT THINKING ABOUT
WHAT YOU SAID, AND...

01:31:05.160 --> 01:31:08.196
I HOPE YOU'RE TRYING
TO MAKE ME STAY AWAY

01:31:08.196 --> 01:31:10.599
FOR MY OWN SAKE.

01:31:10.599 --> 01:31:13.468
NO, IT WAS ACTUALLY
MORE FOR ME.

01:31:13.468 --> 01:31:14.670
OH.

01:31:17.405 --> 01:31:20.408
PETER LEFT ME.

01:31:20.408 --> 01:31:23.679
LEFT YOU?
MMM.

01:31:23.679 --> 01:31:27.983
NO "FUCK YOU."
NO "GOOD-BYE." NO...

01:31:27.983 --> 01:31:30.118
"ARE YOU IN LOVE
WITH GEORGE?"

01:31:34.156 --> 01:31:37.159
WHAT DID HE SAY?

01:31:37.159 --> 01:31:40.162
"I'LL BE
IN THE BEDROOM."

01:31:40.162 --> 01:31:44.266
UM, I COULDN'T
WALK IN THERE, SO HE...

01:31:44.266 --> 01:31:45.934
HE LEFT.

01:31:58.781 --> 01:32:00.583
HEY, DAD,
THE ELECTRICIAN NEEDS TO--

01:32:00.583 --> 01:32:01.784
KNOW...

01:32:03.218 --> 01:32:04.653
AH, I, UM...

01:32:04.653 --> 01:32:05.654
YOUR MOTHER, UM...

01:32:05.654 --> 01:32:06.655
I HAD A KINK IN MY...

01:32:06.655 --> 01:32:08.256
IN HIS NECK.
IN MY BACK.

01:32:08.256 --> 01:32:09.792
NECK.
IN HIS BACK.

01:32:09.792 --> 01:32:11.326
THE DOOR WAS OPEN.

01:32:11.326 --> 01:32:13.361
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'M DOING.

01:32:13.361 --> 01:32:15.831
UM, I WOULDN'T
LET ADAM OR RYAN

01:32:15.831 --> 01:32:17.032
SEE YOU DOING THIS.

01:32:17.032 --> 01:32:17.933
NO.

01:32:17.933 --> 01:32:19.067
George: IT WON'T
HAPPEN AGAIN.

01:32:19.067 --> 01:32:21.870
YEAH, UM, WELL,
DALE WANTS TO KNOW

01:32:21.870 --> 01:32:23.839
IF, UH, IF WE SHOULD
RUN AN OUTSIDE LINE

01:32:23.839 --> 01:32:26.809
FOR CHRISTMAS LIGHTS
WITH A SWITCH INSIDE?

01:32:26.809 --> 01:32:27.943
George: ABSOLUTELY.

01:32:27.943 --> 01:32:29.377
YEAH, AND PUT IT ON
A SEPARATE LINE.

01:32:29.377 --> 01:32:30.813
WE'LL, UM, CHRISTMAS TIME,

01:32:30.813 --> 01:32:31.947
WE'LL PACK IT
SO FULL OF LIGHTS,

01:32:31.947 --> 01:32:34.082
THE NEIGHBORS
WILL NEED SUNGLASSES.

01:32:34.082 --> 01:32:35.150
[CHUCKLES]

01:32:40.288 --> 01:32:44.159
OH, GOD,
I COULD DIE.

01:32:44.159 --> 01:32:45.694
[LAUGHS]

01:32:45.694 --> 01:32:48.163
YEAH, ME, TOO.

01:32:55.437 --> 01:32:58.306
ARE YOU GONNA KISS ME?

01:33:03.411 --> 01:33:05.513
IT'S, UM...

01:33:05.513 --> 01:33:08.183
IT'S NOT MY BACK
THAT'S KILLING ME.

01:34:04.339 --> 01:34:08.276
OH, HELLO.
HOW ARE YOU?

01:34:08.276 --> 01:34:09.377
GOOD.

01:34:12.180 --> 01:34:16.384
GEORGE, I'VE RECRUITED,
UH, HELP FOR THE ROOF.

01:34:16.384 --> 01:34:17.853
HI, GEORGE MONROE.

01:34:17.853 --> 01:34:20.088
JOSH GREY.
ME, TOO.

01:34:24.626 --> 01:34:26.929
NEXT. GRRR.

01:34:26.929 --> 01:34:29.197
I JUST WANTED TO KNOW
WHERE MY MOM WAS.

01:34:29.197 --> 01:34:32.667
I THINK SHE, UH, NEEDS
TO BE ALONE RIGHT NOW.

01:34:32.667 --> 01:34:34.669
BECAUSE DAD LEFT?

01:34:34.669 --> 01:34:36.671
SHE'S JUST A LITTLE SAD,
THAT'S ALL.

01:34:36.671 --> 01:34:38.306
I DON'T CARE
IF HE EVER COMES BACK.

01:34:45.580 --> 01:34:48.150
Alyssa: HERE YOU GO.

01:34:49.818 --> 01:34:51.653
JOSH, YOU LOOK LIKE
YOU NEED A HUG.

01:34:51.653 --> 01:34:53.255
I'M OK.

01:34:55.724 --> 01:34:59.394
THANKS FOR HELPING US.

01:34:59.394 --> 01:35:01.463
DALE.

01:35:01.463 --> 01:35:03.298
DON'T EVEN
THINK ABOUT IT.

01:35:03.298 --> 01:35:04.099
THEY GOT ME STARTED.

01:35:04.099 --> 01:35:06.434
LOOK, I WILL
SHOCK YOU SO BAD

01:35:06.434 --> 01:35:07.970
YOUR TONGUE
WILL TURN BLACK.

01:35:36.999 --> 01:35:40.435
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

01:35:42.737 --> 01:35:44.572
WOULD YOU GET THAT
FOR ME, PLEASE?

01:35:44.572 --> 01:35:45.974
JUST LET MINE RING.

01:35:45.974 --> 01:35:47.442
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

01:35:47.442 --> 01:35:49.611
UH--UH...

01:35:49.611 --> 01:35:51.413
I DON'T KNOW, UH--

01:35:54.449 --> 01:35:55.750
HELLO?

01:35:55.750 --> 01:35:57.319
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:35:57.319 --> 01:36:00.088
YOU ARE DRIVING ME CRAZY,
WAITING LIKE THIS.

01:36:00.088 --> 01:36:03.325
I WANT YOU IN MY BED NOW.

01:36:05.327 --> 01:36:07.095
COLEEN?

01:36:09.464 --> 01:36:11.499
GEORGE?

01:36:11.499 --> 01:36:12.534
IS IT MINE?

01:36:12.534 --> 01:36:14.602
I HOPE NOT.

01:36:14.602 --> 01:36:16.271
COLEEN? HELLO?

01:36:16.271 --> 01:36:18.640
AAH!
OH, SHIT!

01:36:18.640 --> 01:36:19.674
AAH. AAH!

01:36:19.674 --> 01:36:22.477
WHOA. HEY.
OH, JOSH.

01:36:23.678 --> 01:36:25.213
ARE YOU OK?
I'M OK. AAH!

01:36:25.213 --> 01:36:26.982
DON'T MOVE.
DON'T MOVE.

01:36:26.982 --> 01:36:28.650
NO, I'M FINE.
I'M OK.

01:36:28.650 --> 01:36:29.852
WATCH OUT.

01:36:30.953 --> 01:36:32.187
Coleen:
I HEARD A SCREAM.

01:36:32.187 --> 01:36:33.856
JOSH FELL.

01:36:33.856 --> 01:36:35.223
IS THAT A BONE
STICKING OUT?

01:36:35.223 --> 01:36:36.291
George: DON'T MOVE.
DON'T MOVE YOUR NECK.

01:36:36.291 --> 01:36:37.993
I'M GONNA CALL
AN AMBULANCE.

01:36:37.993 --> 01:36:39.027
Josh: I WANNA
JUST STAND UP.

01:36:39.027 --> 01:36:42.865
OW. OW. NO, I'M FINE.
I'M OK.

01:36:42.865 --> 01:36:45.433
[SIREN BLARING]

01:36:54.776 --> 01:36:57.012
A LEG, 2 FINGERS, ONE RIB,

01:36:57.012 --> 01:36:59.747
AND A MILD CONCUSSION.

01:36:59.747 --> 01:37:02.217
NOT BAD,
CONSIDERING THE HEIGHT.

01:37:05.520 --> 01:37:07.822
NOT A PERFECT DAY.

01:37:10.058 --> 01:37:12.360
SHOULD GET THE KIDS HOME.

01:37:13.528 --> 01:37:15.063
COME ON.

01:37:19.601 --> 01:37:21.103
SEE YA.

01:37:26.574 --> 01:37:28.010
SEAT BELT.
OK.

01:37:57.505 --> 01:38:00.442
YOU LOOK LIKE SHIT
LATELY, YOU KNOW?

01:38:00.442 --> 01:38:03.311
YOU'RE LOOKIN'
BETTER THAN EVER.

01:38:06.648 --> 01:38:08.816
YOU KNOW, I DON'T THINK MOM
CARES THAT MUCH

01:38:08.816 --> 01:38:12.087
THAT PETER LEFT.

01:38:12.087 --> 01:38:15.157
SHE SEEMED UPSET.

01:38:17.359 --> 01:38:20.128
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH YOUR BACK?

01:38:22.230 --> 01:38:25.833
I MEAN, DO YOU HAVE
TO HAVE SURGERY ON IT OR WHAT?

01:38:25.833 --> 01:38:27.202
BECAUSE THOSE PILLS
THAT YOU'RE TAKING

01:38:27.202 --> 01:38:29.371
ARE FOR A LOT OF PAIN...

01:38:29.371 --> 01:38:31.306
AND YOU SEEM TO BE
GOING THROUGH 'EM PRETTY QUICK,

01:38:31.306 --> 01:38:33.875
THAT'S ALL.

01:38:33.875 --> 01:38:36.044
YOU'RE NOT STILL
TAKING ANY, ARE YOU?

01:38:36.044 --> 01:38:39.447
NO. NO, BUT I COUNT THEM.

01:38:39.447 --> 01:38:42.985
IN A SOCK ISN'T EXACTLY NEW,
YOU KNOW.

01:38:49.291 --> 01:38:51.626
I'M HAVING A PROBLEM
WITH CANCER.

01:39:00.668 --> 01:39:02.904
I DON'T, UM--

01:39:02.904 --> 01:39:05.373
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS.

01:39:05.373 --> 01:39:06.941
WHAT KIND OF A PROBLEM?

01:39:06.941 --> 01:39:10.612
THE KIND WHERE
THERE ISN'T ANY ANSWER.

01:39:12.947 --> 01:39:15.617
I STILL DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT MEANS.

01:39:16.618 --> 01:39:20.288
SAM, I WANTED US TO--

01:39:20.288 --> 01:39:25.360
GOD, YOU KNOW, SPEND
A FEW MONTHS TOGETHER...

01:39:28.463 --> 01:39:30.432
HERE.

01:39:30.432 --> 01:39:32.434
SOMETIMES THINGS HAPPEN
FOR A REASON.

01:39:32.434 --> 01:39:36.104
YOU KNOW, SOMETHING BAD
TO FORCE SOMETHING GOOD.

01:39:41.509 --> 01:39:43.478
SO, YOU'RE DYING.

01:39:47.315 --> 01:39:50.285
AND YOU TOLD MOM TODAY.

01:40:01.096 --> 01:40:05.400
[WHISPERING]
Fuck you...OK?

01:40:05.400 --> 01:40:07.169
FUCK YOU!

01:40:09.003 --> 01:40:11.306
FUCK YOU!

01:40:17.712 --> 01:40:21.149
YOU KNEW YOU WERE
DYING FROM THE START?

01:40:21.149 --> 01:40:23.085
WE'RE ALL DYING
FROM THE START.

01:40:23.085 --> 01:40:25.553
I JUST GOT MOVED
TO THE HEAD OF THE LINE.

01:40:25.553 --> 01:40:28.223
BUT YOU LIED TO ME.

01:40:28.223 --> 01:40:29.291
I WOULD HAVE LIED
TO MYSELF

01:40:29.291 --> 01:40:31.726
IF I THOUGHT
I'D BELIEVE IT.

01:40:31.726 --> 01:40:33.961
SO, THIS WHOLE THING--

01:40:33.961 --> 01:40:36.831
THIS WHOLE SUMMER
HAVING ME HERE

01:40:36.831 --> 01:40:39.167
WAS FOR YOUR SAKE.

01:40:40.235 --> 01:40:42.337
YOU SELFISH FUCK.

01:40:42.337 --> 01:40:47.041
HAVING ME HERE, TRYING
TO GET ME TO LIKE YOU?

01:40:47.041 --> 01:40:48.710
NO, SAM.

01:40:48.710 --> 01:40:52.714
I WASN'T TRYING TO
GET YOU TO LIKE ME.

01:40:52.714 --> 01:40:55.783
I WAS TRYING TO GET YOU
TO LOVE ME.

01:40:55.783 --> 01:40:57.852
WELL, CONGRATULATIONS...

01:40:57.852 --> 01:41:01.189
'CAUSE YOU FUCKING
PULLED IT OFF!

01:41:06.661 --> 01:41:09.531
YEAH.

01:41:20.142 --> 01:41:21.909
HI, IS ALYSSA HOME?

01:41:21.909 --> 01:41:24.011
IT'S REALLY LATE.

01:41:24.011 --> 01:41:26.181
WHAT'S THE MATTER, SAM?

01:41:26.181 --> 01:41:28.283
NOTHING.

01:41:29.784 --> 01:41:32.320
MY DAD'S DYING.

01:41:34.456 --> 01:41:36.458
I REALLY NEED
TO TALK TO ALYSSA.

01:41:40.662 --> 01:41:43.665
SAM, YOU OK?

01:41:43.665 --> 01:41:50.205
* THAT THERE *

01:41:52.440 --> 01:41:58.713
* THAT'S NOT ME *

01:42:02.016 --> 01:42:08.390
* I'M NOT HERE *

01:42:10.925 --> 01:42:16.231
* THIS ISN'T HAPPENING *

01:42:20.302 --> 01:42:27.141
* I'M NOT HERE *

01:42:27.141 --> 01:42:32.280
* I'M NOT HERE *

01:42:56.804 --> 01:42:58.240
MY DAY OFF.

01:42:59.807 --> 01:43:02.710
THOUGHT I'D HELP OUT
WITH THE PLUMBING.

01:43:02.710 --> 01:43:04.846
MAYBE I'LL FIX
THAT SHOWER FOR YOU.

01:43:04.846 --> 01:43:06.714
THANKS.

01:43:08.450 --> 01:43:09.984
I HAVE A FAVOR TO ASK.

01:43:09.984 --> 01:43:11.686
YOU LOOK LIKE CRAP,
GEORGE.

01:43:11.686 --> 01:43:15.122
I WANT YOU TO FIND
SOMEBODY FOR ME.

01:43:15.122 --> 01:43:17.492
FIND SOMEBODY?

01:43:17.492 --> 01:43:20.562
YEAH, I HAVE SOME
UNFINISHED BUSINESS.

01:43:25.700 --> 01:43:28.436
MR. MONROE?

01:43:28.436 --> 01:43:33.040
MR. MONROE?

01:43:33.040 --> 01:43:34.742
YOU'RE RELENTLESS.

01:43:34.742 --> 01:43:35.710
MR. MONROE,

01:43:35.710 --> 01:43:37.412
ONE OF YOUR NEIGHBORS
IS ADAMANT

01:43:37.412 --> 01:43:39.581
THAT YOUR HOME EXCEEDS
ITS APPROVED HEIGHT,

01:43:39.581 --> 01:43:41.783
AND HE'S FILED
TO HAVE CONSTRUCTION STOPPED

01:43:41.783 --> 01:43:44.151
IMMEDIATELY.

01:43:44.151 --> 01:43:46.288
IT'S 25 FEET.

01:43:46.288 --> 01:43:47.955
WELL, IF IT IS,
WE HAVE A PROBLEM.

01:43:47.955 --> 01:43:49.056
I HAVE THE PERMIT.

01:43:49.056 --> 01:43:50.458
AFTER YOUR LAST
EXTENSION REQUEST,

01:43:50.458 --> 01:43:52.059
AND YOUR APPEALS
TO CITY COUNCIL,

01:43:52.059 --> 01:43:54.061
WAS THERE
AN AMENDED PERMIT?

01:43:54.061 --> 01:43:59.601
YES, FOR THE PATIO,
THE AIR CONDITIONING UNIT...

01:44:02.136 --> 01:44:04.038
AND 6 INCHES TO THE HEIGHT.

01:44:04.038 --> 01:44:05.807
OH.

01:44:05.807 --> 01:44:07.174
DAVID DOKOS?

01:44:07.174 --> 01:44:09.277
WHY DO YOU LET YOUR DOG
CRAP ON HIS LAWN

01:44:09.277 --> 01:44:10.912
DAY AFTER DAY?

01:44:10.912 --> 01:44:12.747
I DON'T LET HIM.

01:44:12.747 --> 01:44:14.716
HE JUST LOVES TO.

01:44:14.716 --> 01:44:16.784
HE'LL MAKE YOU TEAR
THE ENTIRE ROOF OFF

01:44:16.784 --> 01:44:18.553
BEFORE HE'LL GIVE YOU
ANY SATISFACTION.

01:44:18.553 --> 01:44:22.156
UH, LOOK, I'M AFRAID YOU'RE
GONNA HAVE TO STOP ALL THIS

01:44:22.156 --> 01:44:23.758
UNTIL YOU
GET THINGS SETTLED.

01:44:23.758 --> 01:44:25.226
YOU CAN ALWAYS GO BACK
AND FILE AN APPEAL.

01:44:25.226 --> 01:44:27.295
THAT'LL TAKE WEEKS.

01:44:27.295 --> 01:44:29.764
MONTHS.

01:44:29.764 --> 01:44:31.599
JUST SO YOU KNOW,

01:44:31.599 --> 01:44:33.535
WE WILL BE WORKING
ON THIS HOUSE

01:44:33.535 --> 01:44:35.403
TOMORROW AND THE NEXT DAY
AND THE DAY AFTER,

01:44:35.403 --> 01:44:36.504
UNTIL IT'S FINISHED.

01:44:36.504 --> 01:44:37.572
HE'LL CALL US AGAIN,

01:44:37.572 --> 01:44:38.740
AND THEN HE'LL CALL
THE POLICE.

01:44:38.740 --> 01:44:41.042
HE HAS AN ATTORNEY
ON RETAINER.

01:44:41.042 --> 01:44:43.678
JUST SO YOU KNOW.

01:44:44.579 --> 01:44:48.082
IF HE HEARS A HAMMER,
HE'LL HAVE YOU ARRESTED.

01:44:48.082 --> 01:44:52.354
THERE'S--YOU HEARD THE LADY.

01:45:08.035 --> 01:45:09.103
I'M GONNA GO TO BED.

01:45:09.103 --> 01:45:12.306
HAS HE EATEN ANYTHING
AT ALL?

01:45:13.174 --> 01:45:14.642
NO.

01:45:14.642 --> 01:45:16.411
I'D BE MORE COMFORTABLE

01:45:16.411 --> 01:45:18.312
IF HE SLEPT
IN THE GUEST ROOM.

01:45:19.647 --> 01:45:21.115
WELL, I'D BE
MORE COMFORTABLE

01:45:21.115 --> 01:45:23.284
IF YOU HADN'T SLEPT
WITH JOSH.

01:45:23.284 --> 01:45:25.853
GEORGE WOULD
BE MORE COMFORTABLE

01:45:25.853 --> 01:45:27.755
IF HE WASN'T DYING.

01:46:20.041 --> 01:46:22.777
[HAMMERS POUNDING]

01:46:31.218 --> 01:46:32.787
SAM, THERE'S, LIKE,
20 PEOPLE

01:46:32.787 --> 01:46:35.790
WORKING ON YOUR DAD'S HOUSE
RIGHT NOW.

01:46:38.760 --> 01:46:40.595
IF IT WAS MY FATHER,
I'D WANT TO SPEND

01:46:40.595 --> 01:46:43.164
EVERY SINGLE SECOND
WITH HIM.

01:46:44.165 --> 01:46:46.367
YOU HATE YOUR FATHER.

01:46:46.367 --> 01:46:48.069
IF HE TRICKED ME
INTO LOVING HIM

01:46:48.069 --> 01:46:49.971
IS WHAT I MEANT.

01:46:51.405 --> 01:46:54.141
YOU'D HATE HIM
FOR THE TRICK.

01:46:54.942 --> 01:46:57.812
NOT IF WHAT HE LEFT ME
WAS REAL.

01:47:16.498 --> 01:47:18.600
HE PULLED HIS CREW
OFF THE TRACT AT NEWPORT.

01:47:18.600 --> 01:47:19.767
THEY'RE THE BEST.

01:47:19.767 --> 01:47:22.637
THEY'LL STICK WITH IT
TILL IT'S DONE.

01:47:22.637 --> 01:47:25.072
WHAT'S GOING ON?

01:47:25.072 --> 01:47:26.440
I HIRED SOME HELP.

01:47:26.440 --> 01:47:28.075
WHY?

01:47:28.075 --> 01:47:29.110
ATONEMENT.

01:47:29.110 --> 01:47:31.078
MOM.

01:47:31.078 --> 01:47:32.614
WHERE'S GEORGE?

01:47:32.614 --> 01:47:34.649
I THINK HE'S
STILL SLEEPING.

01:47:34.649 --> 01:47:36.718
WHO ARE
ALL THESE PEOPLE?

01:47:36.718 --> 01:47:39.153
I THOUGHT HE NEEDED
SOME HELP.

01:47:47.128 --> 01:47:48.462
GEORGE.

01:47:48.462 --> 01:47:49.931
GEORGE!

01:47:49.931 --> 01:47:51.799
GEORGE, WAKE UP.

01:47:51.799 --> 01:47:53.935
WAKE UP!

01:47:53.935 --> 01:47:56.337
GEORGE,
YOU'RE STILL WARM.

01:47:56.337 --> 01:47:57.672
WAKE UP.

01:47:57.672 --> 01:48:00.207
STOP LICKING ME.

01:48:01.442 --> 01:48:03.878
SAM...

01:48:05.713 --> 01:48:07.782
THEY'RE TAKING YOUR DAD
TO THE HOSPITAL.

01:48:10.317 --> 01:48:11.519
SAM?

01:48:13.320 --> 01:48:16.090
SAM?

01:48:16.090 --> 01:48:18.593
[SIREN WAILING]

01:48:34.341 --> 01:48:36.110
Boy: GUSTER.

01:48:36.110 --> 01:48:38.045
HE IS SHEDDING.

01:48:40.548 --> 01:48:42.550
HEY, GUSTER.

01:48:43.551 --> 01:48:44.552
HEY, BOY.

01:48:44.552 --> 01:48:45.887
I JUST THOUGHT, UH--

01:48:45.887 --> 01:48:48.122
I MEAN, IF YOU'RE HUNGRY,
MAYBE WE COULD, UH...

01:49:09.611 --> 01:49:11.946
YOU DOIN' OK?

01:49:22.757 --> 01:49:25.893
AND WE GOT TO TAKE
ALL THE OLD PAINT OFF,

01:49:25.893 --> 01:49:28.229
EVEN LET ME CHOOSE
THE COLOR I LIKE BEST.

01:49:28.229 --> 01:49:29.664
HE SAID HE LOVED ME.

01:49:29.664 --> 01:49:32.634
AND I GOT TO DRILL
A HOLE FOR A BOARD

01:49:32.634 --> 01:49:34.035
TO PUT THE WIRE
THROUGH.

01:49:34.035 --> 01:49:36.537
NEVER SEEN YOU SO EXCITED
ABOUT ANYTHING.

01:49:36.537 --> 01:49:39.006
WELL, MAYBE
YOU CAN HELP, TOO.

01:49:39.006 --> 01:49:40.708
I'D LIKE THAT.

01:50:07.134 --> 01:50:10.104
AAAAAAAAAAAH!

01:50:39.633 --> 01:50:41.102
EXCUSE ME.

01:50:41.102 --> 01:50:44.271
I'M AFRAID NO ONE'S
ALLOWED IN THERE NOW.

01:50:44.271 --> 01:50:45.873
THAT'S MY FATHER.

01:51:25.312 --> 01:51:26.814
[MOANS]

01:51:27.614 --> 01:51:28.816
HEY.

01:51:32.219 --> 01:51:34.055
HOW ARE YOU FEELING?

01:51:38.025 --> 01:51:41.162
HOW ARE YOU?
YOU'RE WET.

01:51:41.162 --> 01:51:42.429
YEAH, I KNOW.

01:51:42.429 --> 01:51:45.499
WHY? WHY?

01:51:45.499 --> 01:51:48.269
I WENT FOR
A SMALL SWIM.

01:51:48.269 --> 01:51:49.270
OH.

01:51:53.040 --> 01:51:54.976
I WANT TO SHOW YOU
SOMETHING.

01:52:08.722 --> 01:52:12.293
WELL, IT'S
ALMOST FINISHED.

01:52:25.406 --> 01:52:27.274
FINISH IT, SAM.

01:52:36.918 --> 01:52:37.985
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

01:52:37.985 --> 01:52:39.420
I WANT YOU TO GO
STRAIGHT TO BED.

01:52:39.420 --> 01:52:41.155
IT'S LATE.
OK.

01:52:43.925 --> 01:52:46.127
DO YOU KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT BUILDING A HOUSE?

01:52:46.127 --> 01:52:47.128
NOPE.

01:52:47.128 --> 01:52:49.430
I GUESS I COULD TEACH YOU
A FEW THINGS.

01:52:49.430 --> 01:52:50.898
OK.

01:52:55.870 --> 01:52:57.138
SWEET DREAMS.

01:53:00.975 --> 01:53:02.209
[SOFTLY]
Keys, hon.

01:53:02.209 --> 01:53:03.310
THE KEYS, YES.

01:53:06.780 --> 01:53:08.715
YOU'RE NOT
DIFFERENT.

01:53:08.715 --> 01:53:10.417
THAT WAS MY PLAN.

01:53:10.417 --> 01:53:15.056
BE HARDLY RECONIZABLE
TO YOU...AS ME.

01:53:17.158 --> 01:53:19.894
I FELL IN LOVE
WITH GEORGE AGAIN.

01:53:26.600 --> 01:53:27.935
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

01:53:34.208 --> 01:53:37.378
[HAMMERING]

01:53:42.549 --> 01:53:43.951
Alyssa: SAM.

01:53:43.951 --> 01:53:45.486
HEY.
HEY.

01:53:46.487 --> 01:53:47.922
WHERE WERE YOU?

01:53:47.922 --> 01:53:50.024
FLOATING TO CATALINA.

01:53:50.024 --> 01:53:52.559
WHAT?
YOU GOT SOMETHING.

01:53:55.296 --> 01:53:58.699
HE, UH, SAID
HE HEARD HAMMERING.

01:53:58.699 --> 01:54:00.567
WHO?

01:54:00.567 --> 01:54:01.568
MY ATTORNEY'S
DRIVING DOWN

01:54:01.568 --> 01:54:02.636
FROM NEWPORT BEACH,

01:54:02.636 --> 01:54:03.670
AND I JUST WANT YOU
ALL TO KNOW

01:54:03.670 --> 01:54:04.738
THAT IF I HEAR
SO MUCH

01:54:04.738 --> 01:54:05.706
AS ONE MORE NAIL
BEING HAMMERED,

01:54:05.706 --> 01:54:07.008
I SWEAR TO GOD
BY THE TIME

01:54:07.008 --> 01:54:08.109
THIS WHOLE THING'S
OVER,

01:54:08.109 --> 01:54:09.743
I'M GONNA
OWN THIS HOUSE.

01:54:09.743 --> 01:54:11.312
MR. DOKOS CLAIMS
YOUR FATHER

01:54:11.312 --> 01:54:13.414
MISSED HIS HEIGHT
ENVELOPE BY 6 INCHES.

01:54:13.414 --> 01:54:17.018
HE WANTS THE WHOLE ROOF
TAKEN DOWN AND LOWERED.

01:54:19.954 --> 01:54:21.923
WAIT A MINUTE.

01:54:24.858 --> 01:54:26.961
DO YOU DRIVE A, UH,

01:54:26.961 --> 01:54:29.163
A BLACK LEXUS?

01:54:29.163 --> 01:54:30.898
NO.

01:54:33.334 --> 01:54:35.869
THAT'S NOT YOUR CAR OUT
IN THE DRIVEWAY RIGHT THERE?

01:54:39.040 --> 01:54:41.943
I'M GOING BACK TO MY HOUSE
TO WAIT FOR MY LAWYER.

01:54:41.943 --> 01:54:44.745
ARE YOU SURE
WE NEED LAWYERS?

01:54:44.745 --> 01:54:47.881
I MEAN, ALL WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT IS 6 INCHES, RIGHT?

01:54:51.152 --> 01:54:52.219
YOU KNOW, OFFICER,
I THINK WE SHOULD

01:54:52.219 --> 01:54:53.887
JUST FORGET
ALL ABOUT THIS.

01:54:57.758 --> 01:54:59.460
WHAT THE FUCK?

01:55:02.096 --> 01:55:04.131
EVERYTHING HAPPENS
FOR A REASON.

01:55:04.131 --> 01:55:05.532
THAT'S WHAT MY FATHER SAYS.

01:55:05.532 --> 01:55:06.633
WANNA GIVE ME A HAND?

01:55:06.633 --> 01:55:08.235
YEAH.
ALL RIGHT.

01:55:14.541 --> 01:55:16.410
Robin: A WAVE, HE'S--

01:55:16.410 --> 01:55:19.646
HE LOVES IT. [GASP]
THERE'S A BIG ONE.

01:55:21.748 --> 01:55:24.185
OH, HE'S HOLDING ON
SO TIGHT.

01:55:26.620 --> 01:55:32.059
OH. HE'S HALF SCARED
AND HALF LOVING IT.

01:55:36.763 --> 01:55:37.965
HO HO.

01:55:39.733 --> 01:55:42.236
HE HAD SALT
IN HIS EYES.

01:55:45.272 --> 01:55:47.975
THERE. YOU'RE
KISSING HIM.

01:55:51.212 --> 01:55:52.713
YOU'RE SPINNING HIM
RIGHT NOW.

01:55:52.713 --> 01:55:54.215
HE LOVED THAT.

01:55:58.952 --> 01:56:00.721
YOU WERE HAPPY.

01:56:06.527 --> 01:56:07.961
HERE COMES A BIG ONE!

01:56:17.971 --> 01:56:20.274
A REALLY BIG ONE.

01:56:45.566 --> 01:56:47.601
SAM!

01:56:48.602 --> 01:56:50.171
IT'S ALMOST DONE.

01:56:51.205 --> 01:56:53.240
I THOUGHT MAYBE
I COULD HELP, BUT, UH,

01:56:53.240 --> 01:56:56.343
LOOKS LIKE YOU GOT
ALL YOU CAN HANDLE.

01:56:59.080 --> 01:57:01.415
WE COULD ALWAYS USE
AN EXTRA SET OF HANDS.

01:57:16.363 --> 01:57:18.565
YOU SURE WE CAN'T
CALL ANYONE?

01:57:20.033 --> 01:57:21.535
NO, THANK YOU.

01:57:39.720 --> 01:57:42.055
[DRILL WHIRRING]

01:57:42.055 --> 01:57:43.457
HI, MOM.

01:57:51.265 --> 01:57:53.200
IS GEORGE OK?

01:58:13.720 --> 01:58:16.423
George: I ALWAYS THOUGHT
OF MYSELF AS A HOUSE--

01:58:16.423 --> 01:58:19.025
I WAS ALWAYS
WHAT I LIVED IN.

01:58:19.025 --> 01:58:20.627
IT DIDN'T NEED TO BE BIG,

01:58:20.627 --> 01:58:22.829
IT DIDN'T EVEN NEED
TO BE BEAUTIFUL--

01:58:22.829 --> 01:58:24.365
JUST NEEDED TO BE MINE.

01:58:24.365 --> 01:58:28.369
I BECAME WHAT
I WAS MEANT TO BE.

01:58:28.369 --> 01:58:31.905
I BUILT MYSELF A LIFE.

01:58:31.905 --> 01:58:34.275
I BUILT MYSELF A HOUSE.

01:58:34.275 --> 01:58:36.009
THE SECOND TRAILER
ON YOUR RIGHT.

01:58:36.009 --> 01:58:37.378
THANKS.
THANK YOU.

01:58:40.046 --> 01:58:42.449
ARE YOU SURE YOU
WANT TO DO THIS?

01:58:42.449 --> 01:58:44.318
YES.

01:58:44.318 --> 01:58:46.987
YOU COULD KEEP IT
AND RENT IT OUT.

01:58:46.987 --> 01:58:48.689
THIS IS WHAT HE WANTED.

01:58:50.724 --> 01:58:53.026
I READ THE LETTER,
YOU READ THE WILL.

01:58:53.026 --> 01:58:55.196
HE WANTED YOU
TO KEEP IT

01:58:55.196 --> 01:58:57.130
AND LIVE IN IT
SOME DAY.

01:58:57.130 --> 01:58:59.633
ALL RIGHT, MAYBE IT'S NOT
WHAT HE WANTED,

01:58:59.633 --> 01:59:01.768
BUT IT'S WHAT
HE WAS HOPING FOR.

01:59:05.038 --> 01:59:06.773
MAYBE IT'S
WHAT I WANT.

01:59:13.146 --> 01:59:14.481
George: 29 YEARS AGO,

01:59:14.481 --> 01:59:17.218
MY FATHER CROSSED
A DOUBLE LINE.

01:59:17.218 --> 01:59:18.385
EXCUSE ME.

01:59:18.385 --> 01:59:20.086
CHANGED MY LIFE

01:59:20.086 --> 01:59:22.423
AND THE LIFE OF
A LITTLE GIRL FOREVER

01:59:22.423 --> 01:59:23.624
WITH THAT MISTAKE.

01:59:24.758 --> 01:59:27.093
JUST CAN'T STOP
THINKING ABOUT HER.

01:59:27.093 --> 01:59:28.995
UH, DO YOU MIND
IF WE STEAL

01:59:28.995 --> 01:59:30.096
JUST A MOMENT
OF YOUR TIME?

01:59:30.096 --> 01:59:32.733
UM, OK.
HAVE A SEAT.

01:59:32.733 --> 01:59:34.368
THANK YOU.

01:59:39.005 --> 01:59:41.375
MY FATHER
BUILT YOU A HOUSE.

01:59:42.376 --> 01:59:44.811
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

01:59:44.811 --> 01:59:46.913
UH, WELL, MY, UH...

01:59:47.981 --> 01:59:50.217
WELL, MY--
MY FATHER'S FAMILY

01:59:50.217 --> 01:59:52.686
DIED IN A CAR
ACCIDENT, REAL BAD.

02:00:01.728 --> 02:00:04.097
George: WITH EVERY CRASH
OF EVERY WAVE

02:00:04.097 --> 02:00:06.367
I HEAR SOMETHING NOW.

02:00:06.367 --> 02:00:08.702
I NEVER LISTENED BEFORE.

02:00:10.103 --> 02:00:13.874
I'M ON THE EDGE OF A CLIFF,
LISTENING.

02:00:15.342 --> 02:00:16.977
ALMOST FINISHED.

02:00:30.424 --> 02:00:31.858
IF YOU WERE A HOUSE, SAM,

02:00:31.858 --> 02:00:34.094
THIS IS WHERE YOU WOULD
WANT TO BE BUILT--

02:00:34.094 --> 02:00:39.300
ON ROCK, FACING THE SEA.

02:00:39.300 --> 02:00:41.868
LISTENING.

02:00:41.868 --> 02:00:44.237
LISTENING.

